Exerci»õii de seminar 2

Regresie

Obiectivul acestui seminar este de a prezenta c√¢teva exerci»õii de regresie liniarƒÉ.

1 Regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ

1.1 Metoada celor mai mici pƒÉtrate

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ estimatorii \(\hat{\beta}_0\) »ôi \(\hat{\beta}_1\) ob»õinu»õi prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate, adicƒÉ valorile coeficien»õilor \(\beta_0\) »ôi \(\beta_1\) care minimizeazƒÉ func»õia

\[ S(\beta_0, \beta_1) = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \beta_0 - \beta_1 x_i)^2 \]

sunt da»õi de expresiile

\[ \hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x \quad \text{»ôi} \quad \hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

Trebuie sƒÉ determinƒÉm

\[ (\hat{\beta}_0, \hat{\beta}_1) = \underset{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}\times\mathbb{R}}{\arg\min} S(\beta_0, \beta_1) \]

»ôi observ√¢nd cƒÉ func»õia \(S(\beta_0, \beta_1)\) este convexƒÉ ea admite un punct de minim. Acesta se ob»õine ca solu»õie a sistemului \(\nabla S = 0\) de ecua»õi normale,

\[ \left\{\begin{array}{ll} \frac{\partial S}{\partial \beta_0} = -2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \beta_0 - \beta_1 x_i) = 0\\ \frac{\partial S}{\partial \beta_1} = -2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i(y_i - \beta_0 - \beta_1 x_i) = 0 \end{array}\right. \]

Din prima ecua»õie ob»õinem prin sumare \(n\beta_0 + \beta_1\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i = \sum_{i=1}^{n}y_i\) ceea ce conduce la \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\).

A doua ecua»õie conduce la

\[ \beta_0\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i + \beta_1\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}x_iy_i \]

»ôi √Ænlocuind \(\beta_0\) cu expresia ob»õinutƒÉ anterior, ob»õinem solu»õia

\[ \hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i(x_i - \bar x)} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

De asemenea, se poate verifica cƒÉ \(S(\beta_0, \beta_1)\) se scrie sub forma

\[\begin{align*} S(\beta_0, \beta_1) &= n\left[\beta_0 - (\bar y - \beta_1\bar x)\right]^2 + \left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]\left[\beta_1 - \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]^2 \\ &\quad + \left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2\right]\left[1 - \frac{\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)\right)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}\right] \end{align*}\]

care justificƒÉ √Æn egalƒÉ mƒÉsurƒÉ solu»õia ob»õinutƒÉ anterior.

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ estimatorii ob»õinu»õi prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate, \(\hat\beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1\), sunt estimatori nedeplasa»õi.

Coeficien»õii \(\hat\beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1\) ob»õinu»õi prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate sunt da»õi de \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\) (ace»ôtia sunt variabile aleatoare deoarece sunt func»õii de \(Y_i\) care sunt variabile aleatoare). √énlocuind √Æn expresia lui \(\hat\beta_1\) pe \(y_i\) cu \(\beta_0+\beta_1 x_i + \varepsilon_i\) avem

\[\begin{align*} \hat\beta_1 &= \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)y_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(\beta_0+\beta_1 x_i + \varepsilon_i)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ &= \frac{\beta_0\overbrace{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)}^{ = 0} + \beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)x_i + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2 + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ &= \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \end{align*}\]

Conform ipotezei modelului de regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ, \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_i] = 0\), prin urmare \(\mathbb{E}[\hat\beta_1] = \beta_1\) ceea ce aratƒÉ cƒÉ \(\hat\beta_1\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\beta_1\).

√én mod similar,

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat\beta_0] = \mathbb{E}[\bar y] - \bar x\mathbb{E}[\hat\beta_1] = \beta_0 + \bar x\beta_1 - \bar x\beta_1 = \beta_0 \] ceea ce aratƒÉ cƒÉ \(\hat\beta_0\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\beta_0\).

Calcula»õi matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ a estimatorilor \(\hat\beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1\).

NotƒÉm cu \(W = \begin{pmatrix}Var(\hat \beta_0) & Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1)\\ Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1) & Var(\hat \beta_1)\end{pmatrix}\) matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ a estimatorilor \(\hat\beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1\).

Avem, folosind expresia lui \(\hat\beta_1\) determinatƒÉ la punctul anterior »ôi homoscedasticitatea »ôi necorelarea erorilor \(Cov(\varepsilon_i, \varepsilon_j) = \delta_{ij}\sigma^2\), cƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat \beta_1) &= Var\left(\beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right) = Var\left(\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right)\\ &= \frac{Var\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i\right)}{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]^2} = \frac{\sum_{i,j}(x_i - \bar x)(x_j - \bar x)Cov(\varepsilon_i, \varepsilon_j)}{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]^2}\\ &= \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\sigma^2}{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\right]^2} = \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \end{align*}\]

Din expresia \(Var(\hat \beta_1)\) observƒÉm cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(\sigma^2\) este micƒÉ (cu alte cuvinte \(y_i\) sunt aproape de dreapta de regresie) atunci estimarea este mai precisƒÉ. De asemenea, se constatƒÉ cƒÉ pe mƒÉsurƒÉ ce valorile \(x_i\) sunt mai dispersate √Æn jurul valorii medii \(\bar x\) estimarea coeficientului \(\hat \beta_1\) este mai precisƒÉ (\(Var(\hat \beta_1)\) este mai micƒÉ). Acest fenomen se poate observa »ôi √Æn figura de mai jos √Æn care am generat \(100\) de valori aleatoare \(X\) »ôi \(100\) de valori pentru \(Y\) dupƒÉ modelul

\[ y = 1 + 2 x + \varepsilon \] cu \(\varepsilon\sim \mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2)\). Dreapta ro»ôie descrie adevƒÉrata rela»õie \(f(x) = 1 + 2x\) √Æn popula»õie iar dreapta albastrƒÉ reprezintƒÉ dreapta de regresie calculatƒÉ cu ajutorul metodei celor mai mici pƒÉtrate (OLS). Dreptele albastru deschis au fost generate tot cu ajutorul metodei celor mai mici pƒÉtrate atunci c√¢nd variem \(\sigma^2\) (√Æn figura din st√¢nga) »ôi respectiv pe \(x_i\) √Æn jurul lui \(\bar x\) (√Æn figura din dreapta).

Pentru a determina \(Var(\hat \beta_0)\), vom folosi rela»õia \(\hat \beta_0 = \bar y - \hat \beta_1 \bar x\) ceea ce conduce la

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat \beta_0) &= Var(\bar y - \hat \beta_1 \bar x) = Var(\bar y) - 2Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1 \bar x) + Var(\hat \beta_1 \bar x)\\ &= Var\left(\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}y_i\right) - 2\bar x Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1) + \bar x^2 Var(\hat \beta_1)\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{n} + \bar x^2 \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} - 2\bar x Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1). \end{align*}\]

Pentru \(Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1)\) avem (»õin√¢nd cont de faptul cƒÉ \(\beta_0\), \(\beta_1\) »ôi \(x_i\) sunt constante)

\[\begin{align*} Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1) &= Cov\left(\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}y_i, \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2} \right) = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}Cov\left(\beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i + \varepsilon_i, \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\right)\\ &= \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}Cov\left(\varepsilon_i, \frac{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\right) = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}Cov\left(\varepsilon_i, \sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\varepsilon_j\right)\\ &= \frac{1}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{n}\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)Cov(\varepsilon_i, \varepsilon_i=j) = \frac{1}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{n}\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)\delta_{ij}\sigma^2\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{j = 1}^{n}(x_j - \bar x)^2}\frac{1}{n}\underbrace{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)}_{=0} = 0 \end{align*}\]

prin urmare

\[ Var(\hat \beta_0) = \frac{\sigma^2}{n} + \bar x^2 \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} = \frac{\sigma^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}{n\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

Calculul covarian»õei dintre \(\hat \beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat \beta_1\) rezultƒÉ aplic√¢nd rela»õiile de mai sus

\[ Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1) = Cov(\bar y - \hat \beta_1\bar x, \hat \beta_1) = Cov(\bar y, \hat \beta_1) - \bar x Var(\hat \beta_1) = -\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}. \]

ObservƒÉm cƒÉ \(Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1)\leq 0\) iar intuitiv, cum dreapta de regresie (bazatƒÉ pe estimatorii ob»õinu»õi prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate) \(\bar y = \hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) trece prin centrul de greutate al datelor \((\bar x, \bar y)\), dacƒÉ presupunem \(\bar x > 0\) remarcƒÉm cƒÉ atunci c√¢nd cre»ôtem panta (cre»ôtem \(\hat\beta_1\)) ordonata la origine scade (scade \(\hat\beta_0\)) »ôi reciproc.

Matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ a estimatorilor \(\hat\beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1\) devine

\[ W = \begin{pmatrix}Var(\hat \beta_0) & Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1)\\ Cov(\hat \beta_0, \hat \beta_1) & Var(\hat \beta_1)\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\sigma^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}{n\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} & -\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ -\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} & \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\end{pmatrix}. \]

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ √Æn cadrul modelului de regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ, suma valorilor reziduale este nulƒÉ.

ObservƒÉm, folosind defini»õia \(\hat\varepsilon_i = y_i - \hat y_i\), cƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \hat y_i) = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \hat \beta_0 - x_i\hat\beta_1)\\ &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}\left[y_i - \underbrace{(\bar y - \bar x\hat\beta_1)}_{= \hat \beta_0} - x_i\hat\beta_1\right] = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y) -\hat\beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) = 0 \end{align*}\]

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ √Æn modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ statistica \(\hat\sigma^2 = \frac{1}{n-2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\).

»öin√¢nd cont de faptul cƒÉ \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) »ôi \(\bar y = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \bar x + \bar \varepsilon\) (prin √Ænsumarea dupƒÉ \(i\) a rela»õiilor \(y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i +\varepsilon_i\)) gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} \hat\varepsilon_i &= y_i - \hat y_i = (\beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i +\varepsilon_i) - (\hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_i) \\ &= (\underbrace{\bar y - \beta_1 \bar x - \bar \varepsilon}_{=\beta_0} + \beta_1 x_i +\varepsilon_i) - (\bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x + \hat\beta_1 x_i)\\ &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)(x_i - \bar x) + (\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon) \end{align*}\]

»ôi prin dezvoltarea binomului »ôi utiliz√¢nd rela»õia \(\hat\beta_1 = \beta_1 + \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\) gƒÉsim

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2 &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 + 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)\\ &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 + 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\varepsilon_i - 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)\bar\varepsilon\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)\\ &= (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 - 2(\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\\ &=\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2 - (\beta_1 - \hat\beta_1)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2. \end{align*}\]

Lu√¢nd media gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ \mathbb{E}\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2\right) = \mathbb{E}\left(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2\right) - \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2 Var(\hat\beta_1) = (n-1)\sigma^2 - \sigma^2 = (n-1)\sigma^2 \]

unde am folosit cƒÉ \(\mathbb{E}\left(\frac{1}{n-1}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\varepsilon_i - \bar\varepsilon)^2\right) = \sigma^2\) (deoarece \(Var(\varepsilon_i) = \sigma^2\)).

ConcluzionƒÉm cƒÉ \(\hat\sigma^2 = \frac{1}{n-2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat\varepsilon_i^2\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\).

Fie \(x_{n+1}\) o nouƒÉ valoare pentru variabila \(X\) »ôi ne propunem sƒÉ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{n+1} + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\), \(Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\) »ôi \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\).

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ varian»õa rƒÉspunsului mediu prezis este

\[ Var(\hat y_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[\frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right] \]

iar varian»õa erorii de predic»õie \(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1}\) satisface \(\mathbb{E}[\hat\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\) »ôi

\[ Var(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]. \]

Cum \(\hat y_{n+1} = \hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_{n+1}\) avem

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat y_{n+1}) &= Var(\hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_{n+1}) = Var(\hat\beta_0) + 2Cov(\hat\beta_0, \hat\beta_1) + x_{n+1}^2Var(\hat\beta_1)\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}{n\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} - 2\frac{\sigma^2 \bar x}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} + \frac{\sigma^2x_{n+1}^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\left[\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2 - 2x_{n+1}\bar x + x_{n+1}^2\right]\\ &= \frac{\sigma^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\left[\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i -\bar x)^2 + \bar x^2 - 2x_{n+1}\bar x + x_{n+1}^2\right]\\ &= \sigma^2\left[\frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]. \end{align*}\]

ConstatƒÉm cƒÉ atunci c√¢nd \(x_{n+1}\) este departe de valoarea medie \(\bar x\) rƒÉspunsul mediu are o variabilitate mai mare.

Pentru a ob»õine varian»õa erorii de predic»õie \(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1} = y_{n+1} - \hat y_{n+1}\) sƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ \(y_{n+1}\) depinde doar de \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) pe c√¢nd \(\hat y_{n+1}\) depinde de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(i\in\{1,2,\ldots,n\}\). Din necorelarea erorilor deducem cƒÉ

\[ Var(\hat\varepsilon_{n+1}) = Var(y_{n+1} - \hat y_{n+1}) = Var(y_{n+1}) + Var(\hat y_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{(x_{n+1} - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right]. \]

1.2 Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\) »ôi coeficientul de corela»õie

√én aceastƒÉ sec»õiune √ÆncercƒÉm sƒÉ abordƒÉm problema de regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ √Æntr-un context geometric. Din punct de vedere vectorial dispunem de doi vectori: vectorul \(X = (x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n)^\intercal\) a celor \(n\) observa»õii ale variabilei explicative »ôi vectorul \(Y = (y_1, y_2, \ldots, y_n)^\intercal\) compus din cele \(n\) observa»õii ale variabilei rƒÉspuns, pe care vrem sƒÉ o explicƒÉm. Cei doi vectori apar»õin spa»õiului \(\mathbb{R}^n\).

Fie \(\mathbf{1} = (1,1,\ldots,1)^\intercal\in\mathbb{R}^n\) »ôi \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) subspa»õiul liniar din \(\mathbb{R}^n\) de dimensiune \(2\) generat de vectorii \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) (ace»ôti vectori nu sunt coliniari deoarece \(X\) con»õine cel pu»õin douƒÉ elemente distincte). NotƒÉm cu \(\hat Y\) proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(Y\) pe subspa»õiul \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi cum \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) formeazƒÉ o bazƒÉ √Æn \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) deducem cƒÉ existƒÉ \(\hat\beta_0, \hat\beta_1\in \mathbb{R}\) astfel ca \(\hat Y = \hat\beta_0\mathbf{1} + \hat\beta_1 X\). Cum, din defini»õia priec»õiei ortogonale, \(\hat Y\) este unicul vector din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) care minimizeazƒÉ distan»õa euclidianƒÉ (deci »ôi pƒÉtratul ei)

\[ \left\lVert Y - \hat Y \right\rVert = \sum_{i = 1}^{n}[y_i - (\hat\beta_0 + \hat \beta_1 x_i)]^2 \]

deducem cƒÉ \(\hat\beta_0, \hat\beta_1\) coincid cu valorile ob»õinute prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate. Astfel coeficien»õii \(\hat\beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1\) se reprezintƒÉ coordonatele proiec»õiei ortogonale a lui \(Y\) pe subspa»õiul generat de vectorii \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) (a se vedea figura de mai jos).

ObservƒÉm cƒÉ, √Æn general, vectorii \(\{\mathbf{1}, X\}\) nu formeazƒÉ o bazƒÉ ortogonalƒÉ √Æn \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) (cu excep»õia cazului √Æn care \(\langle \mathbf{1}, X\rangle = n\bar x = 0\)) prin urmare \(\hat\beta_0\mathbf{1}\) nu este proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(Y\) pe \(\mathbf{1}\) (aceasta este \(\frac{\langle Y, \mathbf{1}\rangle}{\lVert \mathbf{1}\rVert^2}\mathbf{1} = \bar y\mathbf{1}\)) iar \(\hat\beta_1 X\) nu este proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(Y\) pe \(X\) (aceasta fiind \(\frac{\langle Y, X\rangle}{\lVert X\rVert^2}X\)).

Fie \(\hat\varepsilon = Y - \hat Y = (\hat\varepsilon_1, \hat\varepsilon_2, \ldots, \hat\varepsilon_n)^\intercal\) vectorul valorilor reziduale. Aplic√¢nd Teorema lui Pitagora (√Æn triunghiul albastru) rezultƒÉ (descompunerea ANOVA pentru regresie) cƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} \left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2 &= \left\lVert \hat Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2 + \left\lVert \underbrace{\hat\varepsilon}_{Y - \hat Y}\right\rVert^2\\ \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2 &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar y)^2 + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\underbrace{\hat\varepsilon_i}_{y_i - \hat y_i})^2\\ SS_T &= SS_{reg} + RSS \end{align*}\]

Din defini»õia coeficientului de determinare \(R^2\) avem cƒÉ

\[ R^2 = \frac{SS_{reg}}{SS_T} = \frac{\left\lVert \hat Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2}{\left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{\left\lVert \hat \varepsilon\right\rVert^2}{\left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2} \]

»ôi conform figurii de mai sus \(R^2 = \cos^2(\theta)\). Prin urmare dacƒÉ \(R^2 = 1\), atunci \(\theta = 0\) »ôi \(Y\in\mathcal{M}(X)\), deci \(y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i\), \(i\in\{1,2,\ldots,n\}\) (punctele e»ôantionului sunt perfect aliniate) iar dacƒÉ \(R^2 = 0\), deducem cƒÉ \(\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar y)^2 = 0\), deci \(\hat y_i = \bar y\) (modelul liniar nu este adaptat √Æn acest caz, nu putem explica mai bine dec√¢t media).

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ

\[ R^2 = r_{xy}^2 = r_{y\hat y}^2 \]

unde \(r_{xy}\) este coeficientul de corela»õie empiric dintre \(x\) »ôi \(y\).

Din defini»õia coeficientului de determinare »ôi folosind coeficien»õii \(\hat\beta_0 = \bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\) ob»õinu»õi prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate avem

\[\begin{align*} R^2 &= \frac{\left\lVert \hat Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2}{\left\lVert Y - \bar y \mathbf{1}\right\rVert^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_i - \bar y)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x + \hat\beta_1\bar x - \bar y)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}\\ &= \frac{\hat\beta_1^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = \left(\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\right)^2\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}\\ & = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = r_{xy}^2. \end{align*}\]

Pentru a verifica a doua parte, \(R^2 = r_{y\hat y}^2\), sƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ

\[ r_{y\hat y}^2 = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{\hat y})(y_i - \bar y)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{\hat y})^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} \]

iar \(\bar{\hat y} = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\hat y_i}{n} = \hat \beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 \bar x = \bar y\), prin urmare

\[ r_{y\hat y}^2 = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \bar y)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})^2\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}. \]

De asemenea

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \bar y) &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat y_i + \hat y_i - \bar y) \\ &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat y_i) + \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})^2 \end{align*}\]

»ôi cum

\[\begin{align*} \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat y_i) &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat \beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 x_i - \bar{y})(y_i - \hat \beta_0 - \hat\beta_1 x_i) \\ &= \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\bar y - \hat\beta_1 \bar x + \hat\beta_1 x_i - \bar{y})[(y_i - \bar y ) - \hat\beta_1 (x_i - \bar x)]\\ &= \hat\beta_1 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y) - \hat\beta_1^2 \sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2 \\ &= \underbrace{\frac{S_{xy}}{S_{xx}}}_{\hat\beta_1}S_{xy} - \frac{S_{xy}^2}{S_{xx}^2}S_{xx} = 0 \end{align*}\]

deducem cƒÉ \(r_{y\hat y}^2 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(\hat y_i - \bar{y})^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2} = R^2\).

1.3 Aplica»õii numerice

Tabelul de mai prezintƒÉ o serie de date privind greutatea ta»õilor »ôi respectiv a fiului lor cel mare

\[ \begin{array}{lcccccccccccc} Tata: & 65 & 63 & 67 & 64 & 68 & 62 & 70 & 66 & 68 & 67 & 69 & 71\\ Fiu: & 68 & 66 & 68 & 65 & 69 & 66 & 68 & 65 & 71 & 67 & 68 & 70 \end{array} \]

Ob»õinem urmƒÉtoarele rezultate numerice

\[ \sum_{i = 1}^{12}t_i = 800 \quad \sum_{i = 1}^{12}t_i^2 = 53418 \quad \sum_{i = 1}^{12}t_i f_i = 54107 \quad \sum_{i = 1}^{12}f_i = 811 \quad \sum_{i = 1}^{12}f_i^2 = 54849. \]

  1. Determina»õi dreapta ob»õinutƒÉ prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate a greutƒÉ»õii fiilor √Æn funcie de greutatea ta»õilor.

  2. Determina»õi dreapta ob»õinutƒÉ prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate a greutƒÉ»õii ta»õilor √Æn funcie de greutatea fiilor.

  3. ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ produsul pantelor celor douƒÉ drepte este egal cu pƒÉtratul coeficientului de corela»õie empiricƒÉ dintre \(t_i\) »ôi \(f_i\) (sau coeficientul de determinare).

  1. Dreapta de regresie a greutƒÉ»õii fiilor √Æn func»õie de greutatea ta»õilor este \(f = \hat\alpha_0 + \hat\alpha_1 t\) unde coeficien»õii sunt da»õi de

\[ \hat\alpha_0 = \bar f - \hat\alpha_1 \bar t, \quad \hat\alpha_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(t_i - \bar t)(f_i - \bar f)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(t_i - \bar t)^2} \]

Pentru datele din problema noastrƒÉ coeficien»õii sunt \(\hat\alpha_0 = 35.8\) »ôi \(\hat\alpha_1 = 0.48\) iar dreapta de regresie este \(f = 35.8 + 0.48 t\) (a se vedea figura din st√¢nga).

  1. Dreapta de regresie a greutƒÉ»õii ta»õilor √Æn func»õie de greutatea fiilor este \(t = \hat\beta_0 + \hat\beta_1 f\) unde coeficien»õii sunt da»õi de

\[ \hat\beta_0 = \bar t - \hat\beta_1 \bar f, \quad \hat\beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(f_i - \bar f)(t_i - \bar t)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(f_i - \bar f)^2} \]

√én cazul problemei, coeficien»õii sunt \(\hat\beta_0 = -3.38\) »ôi \(\hat\beta_1 = 1.03\) iar dreapta de regresie este \(t = -3.38 + 1.03 f\) (a se vedea figura din mijloc).

  1. Produsul pantelor celor douƒÉ drepte este

\[ \hat \alpha_1 \hat\beta_1 = \frac{\left[\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(f_i - \bar f)(t_i - \bar t)\right]^2}{\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(f_i - \bar f)^2\sum_{i = 1}^{12}(t_i - \bar t)^2} \]

»ôi conform exerci»õiului 2 »ôi a defini»õiei coeficientului de determinare avem

\[ \hat \alpha_1 \hat\beta_1 = r_{f,t}^2= R^2. \]

Dorim sƒÉ exprimƒÉm √ÆnƒÉl»õimea \(y\) (mƒÉsuratƒÉ √Æn picioare) a unui arbore √Æn func»õie de diametrul sƒÉu \(x\) (exprimat √Æn centimetri) la √ÆnƒÉl»õimea de 1m30 de la sol. Pentru aceasta dispunem de 20 de mƒÉsurƒÉtori \((x_i,y_i)=\)(diametru, √ÆnƒÉl»õime) »ôi √Æn urma calculelor am ob»õinut rezultatele urmƒÉtoare: \(\bar x = 4.53\), \(\bar y = 8.65\) »ôi

\[ \frac{1}{20}\sum_{i = 1}^{20}(x_i - \bar x)^2 = 10.97 \quad \frac{1}{20}\sum_{i = 1}^{20}(y_i - \bar y)^2 = 2.24 \quad \frac{1}{20}\sum_{i = 1}^{20}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y) = 3.77. \]

  1. NotƒÉm cu \(y = \hat \beta_0 + \hat \beta_1 x\) dreapta de regresie. Calcula»õi coeficien»õii \(\hat \beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat \beta_1\).

  2. Da»õi »ôi calcula»õi o mƒÉsurƒÉ care descrie calitatea concordan»õei datelor cu modelul propus.

  3. SƒÉ presupunem cƒÉ abaterile standard pentru estimatorii \(\hat \beta_0\) »ôi \(\hat \beta_1\) sunt \(\hat \sigma_0 = 1.62\) »ôi respectiv \(\hat \sigma_1 = 0.05\). Presupunem cƒÉ erorile \(\varepsilon_i\) sunt variabile aleatoare independente repartizare normal de medie \(0\) »ôi varian»õe egale. Vrem sƒÉ testƒÉm ipotezele \(H_0:\, \beta_j = 0\) versus \(H_1:\, \beta_j \neq 0\) pentru \(j = 0,1\). De ce acest test este interesant √Æn contextul problemei noastre?

  1. Estimatorii coeficien»õilor dreptei de regresie \(y = \hat \beta_0 + \hat \beta_1 x\) sunt da»õi de

\[ \hat \beta_1 = \frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2} \approx 0.344 \]

»ôi respectiv

\[ \hat \beta_0 = \bar y - \hat \beta_1 \bar x \approx 7.09 \]

  1. Pentru a mƒÉsura calitatea concordan»õei datelor la modelul de regresie vom folosi coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\). Am vƒÉzut cƒÉ acesta corespunde pƒÉtratului coeficientului de corela»õie empiricƒÉ:

\[ R^2 = r_{x,y}^2 = \left(\frac{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(y_i - \bar y)}{\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \bar y)^2}}\right)^2 \approx 0.58. \]

ObservƒÉm cƒÉ modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ explicƒÉ un pic mai mult de jumƒÉtate din variabilitatea datelor.

  1. Sub ipoteza modelului condi»õionat normal (erorile \(\varepsilon_i\) sunt variabile aleatoare independente repartizare normal de medie \(0\) »ôi varian»õe egale) avem cƒÉ \(\hat\beta_j\sim\mathcal{N}(\beta_j, \sigma_{\hat\beta_j}^2)\) »ôi √Ænlocuind varian»õele \(\sigma_{\hat\beta_j}^2\) cu estimatorii \(\hat\sigma_j^2\), deducem cƒÉ \(\frac{\hat\beta_j - \beta_j}{\hat\sigma_j}\sim t_{n-2}\).

Prin urmare, sub \(H_0\) avem cƒÉ

\[ \frac{\hat\beta_0}{\hat\sigma_0}\sim t_{18}, \]

iar pentru un prag de semnifica»õie \(1-\alpha = 95\%\), »õin√¢nd seama cƒÉ \(\left|\frac{\hat\beta_0}{\hat\sigma_0}\right|\approx 4.38\) »ôi cƒÉ \(t_{18}(1-\alpha/2)\approx 2.1\), concluzionƒÉm cƒÉ respingem ipoteza nulƒÉ.

√én mod similar, pentru \(\hat\beta_1\) gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ \left|\frac{\hat\beta_1}{\hat\sigma_1}\right|\approx 6.88 > 2.1 \]

de unde respingem ipoteza nulƒÉ \(H_0:\, \beta_1 = 0\) √Æn acest caz de asemenea.

2 Regresie liniarƒÉ multiplƒÉ

Principiul problemei de regresie este de a modela o variabilƒÉ \(y\), numitƒÉ variabilƒÉ rƒÉspuns sau variabilƒÉ dependentƒÉ (cea pe care vrem sƒÉ o explicƒÉm), cu ajutorul unei func»õii care depinde de un anumit numƒÉr de variabile \(\boldsymbol x = (x_1,\ldots, x_p)^\intercal\), numite variabile explicative sau predictori sau independente (vom folosi √Æn general primele douƒÉ denumiri)

\[ y\approx g(\boldsymbol x) = g(x_1,\ldots, x_p). \] Astfel av√¢nd dat un e»ôantion de talie \(n\) de \((p+1)\)-upluri \((\boldsymbol x, y)\), \(n>p\), ne propunem sƒÉ determinƒÉm \(g\). Aproximarea, \(\approx\), din rela»õia anterioarƒÉ se poate descrie matematic sub forma

\[ g = \underset{f\in\mathcal{G}}{\arg\min}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}L\left(y_i - f(\boldsymbol x_i)\right) \]

unde \(L(\cdot)\) se nume»ôte func»õie de cost sau de pierdere iar \(\mathcal{G}\) este o clasƒÉ de func»õii datƒÉ.

√én general func»õia de cost poate lua multe forme, e.g.¬†Loss function, dar de cele mai multe ori vom √Ænt√¢lni douƒÉ: func»õia de cost absolut \(L(x) = |x|\) sau func»õia de cost pƒÉtratic \(L(x) = x^2\).

√én ceea ce prive»ôte clasa de func»õii \(\mathcal{G}\) vom considera func»õiile liniare

\[ \mathcal{G} = \left\{f:\mathbb{R}^p\to \mathbb{R}\,|\, f(\boldsymbol x) = \begin{pmatrix}1 & \boldsymbol x\end{pmatrix} \boldsymbol \beta = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_1 +\cdots + \beta_p x_p\right\}. \]

Atunci c√¢nd vorbim de regresie liniarƒÉ ne referim la liniaritatea √Æn parametrii \(\beta_j\) »ôi nu √Æn variabilele explicative, e.g.¬†\(f_1(x_1,x_2) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_1 + \beta_2 x_2\), \(f_2(x_1, x_2) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_1 + \beta_2 x_2 + \beta_3 \underbrace{x_1 x_2}_{x_3}\) sau \(f_3(x_1, x_2) = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_1 + \beta_2 x_2 + \beta_3 \underbrace{x_1 x_2}_{x_3}+ \beta_4 \underbrace{x_1^2}_{x_4}+ \beta_5 \underbrace{x_2^3}_{x_5}\) sunt toate func»õii liniare √Æn \(\boldsymbol\beta\).

2.1 Modelare

Modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ multiplƒÉ reprezintƒÉ o extensie a modelului de regresie liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ atunci c√¢nd numƒÉrul variabilelor explicative este finit (pentru mai multe detalii privind analiza de regresie se pot consulta monografiile (Seber and Lee 2003), (Weisberg 2014) sau (Faraway 2015)). Presupunem cƒÉ datele verificƒÉ modelul

\[ y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{i1} + \cdots + \beta_p x_{ip} + \varepsilon_i, \quad i = 1,2,\ldots,n \] unde

  • \(x_{ij}\) sunt valori cunoscute »ôi nu sunt aleatoare

  • parametrii \(\beta_j\) sunt necunoscu»õi »ôi nu sunt aleatori

  • \(\varepsilon_i\) sunt variabile aleatoare necunoscute

Scris sub formƒÉ compactƒÉ modelul devine

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon \]

unde

  • \(\mathbf{X}\) se nume»ôte matricea de design

\[ \mathbf{X}=\begin{pmatrix} 1 & x_{11} & \cdots & x_{1p}\\ \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ 1 & x_{n1} & \cdots & x_{np} \end{pmatrix}_{n\times(p+1)} \]

  • \(\mathbf{Y}\) este vectorul rƒÉspuns »ôi este un vector aleator, \(\boldsymbol\beta\) este vectorul parametrilor sau coeficien»õilor »ôi este necunoscut iar \(\boldsymbol\varepsilon\) este vectorul erorilor »ôi este un vector aleator

\[ \mathbf{Y}=\begin{pmatrix} Y_1 \\ \vdots \\ Y_n \end{pmatrix}_{n\times 1},\quad\boldsymbol\beta=\begin{pmatrix} \beta_0 \\ \beta_1 \\ \vdots \\ \beta_p \end{pmatrix}_{(p+1)\times 1}\text{ »ôi }\quad \boldsymbol\varepsilon=\begin{pmatrix} \varepsilon_1 \\ \vdots \\ \varepsilon_n \end{pmatrix}_{n\times 1}. \]

Ipotezele modelului de regresie liniarƒÉ multiplƒÉ sunt:

\[ \begin{array}{ll} \mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\\ \mathcal{H}_2: \, \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon] = 0,\, Var(\boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n \end{array} \]

Prima ipotezƒÉ ne spune cƒÉ matricea de design \(\boldsymbol X\) are coloanele liniar independente iar a doua ipotezƒÉ se referƒÉ la centralitatea erorilor (medie nulƒÉ), homoscedasticitatea (aceea»ôi varian»õƒÉ) »ôi necorelarea acestora.

2.2 Metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate

√én aceastƒÉ sec»õiune vom prezenta estimatorul lui \(\boldsymbol \beta\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate, metodƒÉ care folose»ôte ca func»õie de cost \(L\) func»õia \(L(x) = x^2\). Estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate este definit prin

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \underset{\boldsymbol\beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}}{\arg\min}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\left[y_i - \left(\beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{i1} + \cdots + \beta_p x_{ip}\right)\right]^2 = \underset{\boldsymbol\beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}}{\arg\min}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}\left(y_i - \sum_{j= 0}^{p}\beta_j x_{ij}\right)^2 = \underset{\boldsymbol\beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}}{\arg\min}\left\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\right\rVert^2 \]

unde am folosit conven»õia \(x_{i0} = 1\), \(i = 1,2,\ldots,n\).

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ dacƒÉ ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_1\) este adevƒÉratƒÉ atunci estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate este

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y \]

Ne propunem sƒÉ prezentƒÉm mai multe metode de calcul pentru estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\).

  1. Metoda geometricƒÉ

Din punct de vedere geometric, ne plasƒÉm √Æn spa»õiul variabilelor \(\mathbb{R}^n\) (am presupus cƒÉ \(n>p\))). Vectorul variabilelor rƒÉspuns \(\boldsymbol Y\in \mathbb{R}^n\) iar matricea de design \(\boldsymbol{X}\) poate fi vƒÉzutƒÉ ca fiind formatƒÉ din \(p+1\) vectori coloanƒÉ, \(\boldsymbol{X} = \left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol X_0}_{\mathbf{1} = (1,\cdots,1)}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\).

√éncepem prin a reaminti c√¢teva no»õiuni de algebrƒÉ liniarƒÉ, pentru mai multe detalii se poate consulta monografia (Ornea and Turtoi 2000). Fiind datƒÉ matricea (de design) \(\boldsymbol{X}\in\mathcal{M}_{n,p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) putem defini nucleul matricei

\[ \ker(\boldsymbol{X}) = \left\{\boldsymbol u\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\,|\, \boldsymbol{X}\boldsymbol u = 0\right\} \]

ca fiind subspa»õiul lui \(\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) care con»õine vectorii ortogonali pe liniile din matricea \(\boldsymbol{X}\). De asemenea, imaginea matricei \(\boldsymbol{X}\) este subspa»õiul vectorilor din \(\mathbb{R}^n\) care se pot scrie ca o combina»õie liniarƒÉ de coloanele matricei \(\boldsymbol{X}\) »ôi este definit prin

\[ \mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X}) = \left\{\boldsymbol v\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\,|\,\exists \boldsymbol u\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1} \text{ a.√Æ. } \boldsymbol{X}\boldsymbol u = \boldsymbol v\right\}. \]

Se poate arƒÉta (a se vedea (Ornea and Turtoi 2000, Capitolul 1)) cƒÉ \(\dim \ker(\boldsymbol{X}) = p + 1 - \mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol{X})\) »ôi cƒÉ \(\dim \mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X}) = \mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol{X})\) ceea ce conduce la \(\dim \ker(\boldsymbol{X}) + \dim \mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X}) = p+1\) (caz particular al teoremei lui Grassman).

Reamintim cƒÉ doi vectori \(\boldsymbol u\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol v\) sunt ortogonali dacƒÉ \(\langle \boldsymbol u, \boldsymbol v\rangle = 0\), iar √Æn acest caz scriem \(\boldsymbol u \perp \boldsymbol v\), »ôi cƒÉ douƒÉ subspa»õii \(V\) »ôi \(W\) sunt ortogonale dacƒÉ \(\forall \boldsymbol v \in V\) »ôi respectiv \(\forall \boldsymbol w \in W\) avem \(\boldsymbol v\perp \boldsymbol w\) »ôi notƒÉm \(V\perp W\). De asemenea, spa»õiul ortogonal al lui \(V\) este spa»õiul \(V^{\perp}\) care con»õine to»õi vectorii ortogonali pe \(V\) »ôi are ca proprietƒÉ»õi: \(V\cap V^{\perp} = \{0\}\) »ôi \(\left(V^{\perp}\right)^\perp = V\). Se poate arƒÉta cu u»ôurin»õƒÉ cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(V\) este un subspa»õiu a lui \(W\subset\mathbb{R}^n\) atunci pentru orice vector \(\boldsymbol w\in W\) avem cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol w = \boldsymbol v + \boldsymbol v^\perp\) unde \(\boldsymbol v\in V\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol v^\perp\in V^\perp\) iar descompunerea se face √Æn mod unic (acest rezultat se mai scrie »ôi sub forma \(W = V\oplus V^\perp\)). Se nume»ôte proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ1 a lui \(\boldsymbol w\) pe \(V\) de-a lungul lui \(V^\perp\) endomorfismul \(p_V: W\to W\) definit prin \(p_V(\boldsymbol w) = \boldsymbol v\). Se poate arƒÉta cu u»ôurin»õƒÉ cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(V\) este un subspa»õiu vectorial al lui \(W\) atunci au loc urmƒÉtoarele proprietƒÉ»õi:

  1. pentru orice \(\boldsymbol w\in W\) avem: \(\boldsymbol w = p_V(\boldsymbol w) + p_{V^\perp}(\boldsymbol w)\), \(\lVert p_V(\boldsymbol w)\rVert \leq \lVert \boldsymbol w\rVert\) iar \(\boldsymbol w - p_{V}(\boldsymbol w) \perp \boldsymbol v\), \(\forall \boldsymbol v \in V\)

  2. pentru orice \(\boldsymbol w\in W\) are loc \(\lVert \boldsymbol w - p_V(\boldsymbol w)\rVert = \inf_{\boldsymbol v\in V}\lVert \boldsymbol w - \boldsymbol v\rVert\)

  3. dacƒÉ \(p\) este o proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ atunci \(p\circ p = p\)

  4. dacƒÉ \(p\) este un endomorfism care verificƒÉ \(p\circ p = p\) »ôi √Æn plus \(\textrm{Im}(p)\perp \ker(p)\) atunci \(p\) este proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\textrm{Im}(p)\) de-a lungul lui \(\ker(p)\)

  5. dacƒÉ \(\{\boldsymbol e_1, \boldsymbol e_2, \ldots, \boldsymbol e_k\}\) este o bazƒÉ ortonormalƒÉ √Æn \(V\) atunci \(p_V(\boldsymbol w) = \sum_{i = 1}^{k}\langle \boldsymbol w, \boldsymbol e_i\rangle \boldsymbol e_i\)

Spunem cƒÉ o matrice pƒÉtraticƒÉ \(P\in\mathcal{M}_{n}(\mathbb{R})\) este o matrice de proiec»õie dacƒÉ este idempotentƒÉ \(P^2 = P\) (numele vine de la faptul cƒÉ pentru \(\boldsymbol x\in\mathbb{R}^n\) aplica»õia liniarƒÉ \(P\boldsymbol x\) este proiec»õia lui \(\boldsymbol x\) pe \(\mathrm{Im}(P)\) de-a lungul lui \(\ker(P)\) - a se vedea (Ornea and Turtoi 2000, Capitolul 1, Sec»õiunea 5.2) sau (Yanai, Takeuchi, and Takane 2011, Capitolul 2)). DacƒÉ √Æn plus matricea \(P\) este simetricƒÉ, i.e.¬†\(P = P^\intercal\), atunci \(P\boldsymbol x\) este proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(\boldsymbol x\) pe \(V = \mathrm{Im}(P)\) de-a lungul lui \(V^\perp = \ker(P)\), cu alte cuvinte √Æn descompunerea \(\boldsymbol x = P\boldsymbol x + (I - P)\boldsymbol x\) vectorii \(P\boldsymbol x\) »ôi respectiv \((I - P)\boldsymbol x\) sunt ortogonali (Yanai, Takeuchi, and Takane 2011, Capitolul 2, Sec»õiunea 2.2). Prin urmare matricea \(P\) este o matrice de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ dacƒÉ are loc rela»õia \(\boldsymbol v\perp \boldsymbol v - P\boldsymbol v\) adicƒÉ \(\langle\boldsymbol v, \boldsymbol v - P\boldsymbol v\rangle = 0\) pentru to»õi \(\boldsymbol v\).

DacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol{X}\in\mathcal{M}_{m,k}(\mathbb{R})\) este o matrice de \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol{X}) = k\) (\(m\geq k\)), deci \(\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal\boldsymbol{X}\) este inversabilƒÉ, atunci pentru a determina matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ \(P_X\) pe subspa»õiul imagine \(\mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X})\) sƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol v\in \textrm{Im}(\boldsymbol X)\) atunci \(\boldsymbol v = \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol \alpha\) »ôi cum \(P_X \boldsymbol v = \boldsymbol v\) deducem cƒÉ \(P_X \boldsymbol v = \boldsymbol{X}\underbrace{\left(\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal\boldsymbol{X}\right)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol v}_{= \boldsymbol \alpha}\). √én plus dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol v^\perp\in \textrm{Im}(\boldsymbol X)^\perp = \ker(\boldsymbol X^\intercal)\) atunci \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol v^\perp = 0\) prin urmare \(\boldsymbol{X}\left(\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal\boldsymbol{X}\right)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol v^\perp = 0\) »ôi astfel, pentru \(\boldsymbol w = \boldsymbol v + \boldsymbol v^\perp\) arbitrar, avem \(P_{X}\boldsymbol w = \boldsymbol{X}\left(\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal\boldsymbol{X}\right)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal\boldsymbol w\) de unde gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ P_{X} = \boldsymbol{X}\left(\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal\boldsymbol{X}\right)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal. \]

√én mod similar se aratƒÉ cƒÉ matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\ker(\boldsymbol{X})\) este \(P_{X\perp} = I - P_{X}\). Nu este dificil de vƒÉzut cƒÉ cele douƒÉ matrice, \(P_{X}\) »ôi respectiv \(P_{X\perp}\), sunt idempotente. De asemenea, »õin√¢nd seama cƒÉ valorile proprii ale unei matrice idempotente sunt \(0\) sau \(1\) concluzionƒÉm cƒÉ \(\mathrm{rang}(P_X) = \mathrm{Tr}(P_X)\).

√én cazul particular √Æn care \(\boldsymbol{X} = \boldsymbol{v}\) avem

\[ P_v = \boldsymbol{v}\left(\boldsymbol{v}^\intercal\boldsymbol{v}\right)^{-1}\boldsymbol{v}^\intercal = \frac{\boldsymbol{v}\boldsymbol{v}^\intercal}{\lVert\boldsymbol{v}\rVert^2} \]

prin urmare proiec»õia vectorului \(\boldsymbol{u}\) pe \(\boldsymbol{v}\) este \(P_v\boldsymbol{u} = \frac{\boldsymbol{v}\boldsymbol{v}^\intercal}{\lVert\boldsymbol{v}\rVert^2}\boldsymbol{u} = \frac{\langle\boldsymbol{u}, \boldsymbol{v}\rangle}{\lVert\boldsymbol{v}\rVert^2}\boldsymbol{v}\).

Pentru problema noastrƒÉ, notƒÉm cu \(\mathcal{M}(X) = \mathrm{Im}(\boldsymbol{X})\) subspa»õiul imagine »ôi conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_1\) avem cƒÉ \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol{X}) = p+1\), deci \(\dim \mathcal{M}(X) = p+1\). Din defini»õia spa»õiului imagine avem cƒÉ to»õi vectorii din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) sunt de forma \(\boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\alpha\), cu \(\boldsymbol \alpha = (\alpha_0, \alpha_1,\ldots, \alpha_p)\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\)

\[ \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\alpha = \sum_{i = 0}^{p}\alpha_i \boldsymbol X_i. \]

Conform modelului de regresie, \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\), vectorul rƒÉspuns \(\boldsymbol Y\) este suma dintre un element din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi un element din \(\mathbb{R}^n\) care nu are niciun motiv sƒÉ apar»õinƒÉ tot lui \(\mathcal{M}(X)\). Astfel, problema minimizƒÉrii func»õiei \(S(\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\right\rVert^2\) revine la a gƒÉsi acel vector din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) care este cel mai aproape de \(\boldsymbol Y\) √Æn sensul distan»õei euclidiene, cu alte cuvinte de a determina vectorul proiec»õiei ortogonale a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) (a se vedea figura de mai jos).

Proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) se noteazƒÉ cu \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = P_X \boldsymbol Y\), unde \(P_X\) este matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\), iar spa»õiul ortogonal \(\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) se mai nume»ôte »ôi spa»õiul reziduurilor »ôi are dimensiunea \(\dim \mathcal{M}(X)^\perp = n - (p+1)\) (teorema lui Grassman). SƒÉ remarcƒÉm cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}\in\mathcal{M}(X)\) deci putem scrie \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) unde \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) reprezintƒÉ estimatorul ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate iar elementele lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) sunt coordonatele vectorului \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) √Æn baza \(\{\boldsymbol X_0, \boldsymbol X_1,\ldots, \boldsymbol X_p\}\) a spa»õiului \(\mathcal{M}(X)\). Cum reperul \(\{\boldsymbol X_0, \boldsymbol X_1,\ldots, \boldsymbol X_p\}\) nu este neapƒÉrat ortogonal, elementele \(\hat{\beta_j}\) nu sunt neapƒÉrat coordonatele proiec»õiei lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\boldsymbol X_j\), aceasta din urmƒÉ fiind datƒÉ de

\[\begin{align*} P_{X_j}\boldsymbol Y &= P_{X_j}P_X \boldsymbol Y = P_{X_j}\sum_{i = 0}^{p} \hat{\beta_i}\boldsymbol X_i\\ &= \sum_{i = 0}^{p}\hat{\beta_i} P_{X_j}\boldsymbol X_i = \hat{\beta_j} \boldsymbol X_j + \sum_{i \neq j}\hat{\beta_i} P_{X_j}\boldsymbol X_i \end{align*}\]

√én cazul √Æn care \(\boldsymbol X_j\) este ortogonal pe \(\boldsymbol X_i\), \(i\neq j\), atunci \(P_{X_j}\boldsymbol Y = \hat{\beta_j} \boldsymbol X_j\) iar dacƒÉ \(\langle\boldsymbol X_i, \boldsymbol X_j\rangle = 0\) pentru to»õi \(i\neq j\) atunci matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \mathrm{diag}\left(\lVert\boldsymbol X_0\rVert^2, \lVert\boldsymbol X_1\rVert^2, \ldots, \lVert\boldsymbol X_p\rVert^2\right)\).

O altƒÉ metodƒÉ (tot prin proiec»õii) de a arƒÉta cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\) se bazeazƒÉ pe observa»õia cƒÉ proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este definitƒÉ ca fiind unicul vector pentru care \(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) este ortogonal pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\). Cum \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) este generat de \(\{\boldsymbol X_0, \boldsymbol X_1,\ldots, \boldsymbol X_p\}\) putem spune cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) este ortogonal pe fiecare \(\boldsymbol X_i\):

\[ \left\{\begin{array}{lll} \langle \boldsymbol X_0, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rangle = 0\\ \langle \boldsymbol X_1, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rangle = 0\\ \vdots\\ \langle \boldsymbol X_p, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rangle = 0 \end{array}\right. \iff \left\{\begin{array}{lll} \langle \boldsymbol X_0, \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\rangle = 0\\ \langle \boldsymbol X_1, \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\rangle = 0\\ \vdots\\ \langle \boldsymbol X_p, \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\rangle = 0 \end{array}\right. \iff \boldsymbol X^\intercal \left(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) = 0 \]

de unde gƒÉsim sistemul de ecua»õii normale

\[ \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y \]

care, atunci c√¢nd ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_1\) este adevƒÉratƒÉ - matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este inversabilƒÉ, revine la

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y. \]

Not√¢nd cu \(P_{X^\perp} = I_n - P_X\) matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}^\perp(X)\), unde \(P_X = \boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal\) este matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\), observƒÉm cƒÉ descompunerea

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \hat{\boldsymbol Y} + \left(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\right) = P_X\boldsymbol Y + (I - P_X)\boldsymbol Y = P_X\boldsymbol Y + P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y \]

nu este altceva dec√¢t descompunerea ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi respectiv \(\mathcal{M}^\perp(X)\). De asemenea este de remarcat faptul cƒÉ √Æn ceea ce prive»ôte nota»õia folositƒÉ √Æn literatura de statisticƒÉ de specialitate, matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ \(P_X\) se mai noteazƒÉ »ôi cu \(H\) (care vine de la hat, \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = H\boldsymbol Y\)).

  1. Metoda analiticƒÉ

O a doua metodƒÉ este metoda analiticƒÉ. Problema noastrƒÉ cere sƒÉ cƒÉutƒÉm vectorul \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) care minimizeazƒÉ func»õia

\[\begin{align*} S(\boldsymbol \beta) &= \left\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\right\rVert^2 = \left(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\right)^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\right) = \boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta - \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y + \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta \\ & = \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta - 2 \boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta + \lVert \boldsymbol Y \rVert^2 \end{align*}\]

unde am folosit faptul cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta = \left(\boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\right)^\intercal = \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\) (sunt elemente de dimensiune \(1\times 1\)). Pentru aceasta trebuie sƒÉ rezolvƒÉm ecua»õia \(\nabla S(\boldsymbol \beta) = 0\) »ôi sƒÉ verificƒÉm cƒÉ solu»õia este √Æntr-adevƒÉr punct de minim.

Reamintim cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(f:\mathbb{R}^k\to\mathbb{R}\) atunci

\[ \nabla f = \frac{\partial f}{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal} = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\partial f}{\partial x_1} & \frac{\partial f}{\partial x_2} & \cdots & \frac{\partial f}{\partial x_k}\end{pmatrix}. \]

√én particular, pentru \(f(\boldsymbol x) = \boldsymbol a^\intercal \boldsymbol x\) (formƒÉ liniarƒÉ) avem

\[ \nabla f = \frac{\partial \boldsymbol a^\intercal \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal} = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\partial \sum_{i=1}^{k}a_i x_i}{\partial x_1} & \frac{\partial \sum_{i=1}^{k}a_i x_i}{\partial x_2} & \cdots & \frac{\partial \sum_{i=1}^{k}a_i x_i}{\partial x_k}\end{pmatrix} = \boldsymbol a^\intercal \]

iar \(\frac{\partial \boldsymbol a^\intercal \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x} = \boldsymbol a\).

√én cazul √Æn care \(f\) este o aplica»õie liniarƒÉ, \(f(\boldsymbol x) = A \boldsymbol x\) unde \(A\in\mathcal{M}_{m,k}(\mathbb{R})\), atunci

\[ A \boldsymbol x = \begin{pmatrix}\sum_{j=1}^{k}a_{1j} x_j\\ \sum_{j=1}^{k}a_{2j} x_j\\ \vdots\\ \sum_{j=1}^{k}a_{mj} x_j\end{pmatrix}, \qquad \frac{\partial A \boldsymbol x}{\partial x_j} = \begin{pmatrix}a_{1j}\\ a_{2j}\\ \vdots\\ a_{mj}\end{pmatrix} \]

»ôi

\[ \frac{\partial A \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal} = \begin{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}a_{11}\\ a_{21}\\ \vdots\\ a_{m1}\end{pmatrix}, \ldots, \begin{pmatrix}a_{1j}\\ a_{2j}\\ \vdots\\ a_{mj}\end{pmatrix}, \ldots, \begin{pmatrix}a_{1k}\\ a_{2k}\\ \vdots\\ a_{mk}\end{pmatrix}\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}a_{11} & \cdots & a_{1j} & \cdots & a_{1k}\\ \vdots & \ddots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ a_{i1} & \cdots & a_{ij} & \cdots & a_{ik}\\ \vdots & \ddots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ a_{m1} & \cdots & a_{mj} & \cdots & a_{mk} \end{pmatrix} = A. \]

√én mod similar se poate verifica »ôi rela»õia \(\frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A^\intercal}{\partial \boldsymbol x} = A^\intercal\).

DacƒÉ \(f\) este o formƒÉ pƒÉtraticƒÉ \(f(\boldsymbol x) = \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x\) cu \(A\in\mathcal{M}_{k}(\mathbb{R})\) (matrice pƒÉtraticƒÉ de ordin \(k\)), atunci

\[ \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x = \sum_{i = 1}^{k}\sum_{j = 1}^{k}a_{ij}x_ix_j = \sum_{i = 1}^{k}a_{ii}x_i^2 + \sum_{i = 1}^{k}\sum_{\substack{j = 1\\ j\neq i}}^{k}a_{ij}x_ix_j \]

de unde

\[ \frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial x_r} = 2 a_{rr}x_r + \sum_{j\neq r}a_{rj}x_j + \sum_{i\neq r}a_{ir}x_i = \sum_{j = 1}^{k}a_{rj}x_j + \sum_{i = 1}^{k}a_{ir}x_i \]

prin urmare

\[ \frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x} = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial x_1}\\ \vdots\\ \frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial x_k}\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\sum_{j = 1}^{k}a_{1j}x_j + \sum_{i = 1}^{k}a_{i1}x_i\\ \vdots\\ \sum_{j = 1}^{k}a_{kj}x_j + \sum_{i = 1}^{k}a_{ik}x_i\end{pmatrix} = A\boldsymbol x + A^\intercal \boldsymbol x. \]

De asemenea putem observa cƒÉ \(\frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal} = \left(A\boldsymbol x + A^\intercal \boldsymbol x\right)^\intercal = \boldsymbol x^\intercal A^\intercal + \boldsymbol x^\intercal A\).

√én plus, dacƒÉ \(A\in\mathcal{M}_{k}(\mathbb{R})\) este o matrice simetricƒÉ (\(A^\intercal = A\)) atunci

\[ \frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x} = 2A\boldsymbol x, \quad \frac{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal A \boldsymbol x}{\partial \boldsymbol x^\intercal} = 2\boldsymbol x^\intercal A^\intercal. \]

Revenind la problema noastrƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ \(S(\boldsymbol \beta)\) este pƒÉtraticƒÉ √Æn \(\boldsymbol \beta\) iar matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este simetricƒÉ, prin urmare

\[ \nabla S(\boldsymbol \beta) = \frac{\partial S(\boldsymbol \beta)}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal} = \frac{\partial }{\partial \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal}\left(\boldsymbol \beta^\intercal \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta - 2 \boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta + \lVert \boldsymbol Y \rVert^2\right) = 2 \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X) - 2 \boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X = 0 \]

este echivalentƒÉ cu sistem de ecua»õii normale (prin trecerea la transpusƒÉ)

\[ (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)\boldsymbol \beta = \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y \]

care atunci c√¢nd ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_1\) este adevƒÉratƒÉ, ceea ce conduce la inversabilitatea matricei \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) (are valori proprii nenule), revine la

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y. \]

Pentru a arƒÉta cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este √Æntr-adevƒÉr un punct de minim pentru \(S(\boldsymbol \beta)\) trebuie sƒÉ arƒÉtƒÉm cƒÉ matricea hessianƒÉ este pozitiv definitƒÉ. Matricea hessianƒÉ, »õin√¢nd cont de simetria matricii \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\), este

\[ \frac{\partial^2 S(\boldsymbol \beta)}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta\partial \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal} = \frac{\partial}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta}\left(\frac{\partial S(\boldsymbol \beta)}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal}\right) = \frac{\partial}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta}\left(2 \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X) - 2 \boldsymbol Y^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right) = 2 \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X \]

iar pentru \(\boldsymbol u\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\backslash\{0\}\) avem

\[ \boldsymbol u^\intercal \frac{\partial^2 S(\boldsymbol \beta)}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta\partial \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal} \boldsymbol u = \boldsymbol u^\intercal \left(2 \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right) \boldsymbol u = \langle \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol u, \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol u\rangle = 2\lVert \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol u\rVert^2 > 0 \]

deci \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este pozitiv definitƒÉ prin urmare »ôi \(\frac{\partial^2 S(\boldsymbol \beta)}{\partial \boldsymbol \beta\partial \boldsymbol \beta^\intercal}\) este pozitiv definitƒÉ.

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ dacƒÉ ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2\) sunt adevƒÉrate atunci estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate este nedeplasat, i.e.¬†\(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol \beta\) iar matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(Var\left(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right)\) este

\[ Var\left(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) = \sigma^2 \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)^{-1}. \]

Pentru √Ænceput, deoarece vorbim de opera»õii cu vectori aleatori sau matrice aleatoare, vom reaminti c√¢teva proprietƒÉ»õi de calcul a acestora (acestea generalizeazƒÉ no»õiunile corespunzƒÉtoare din cazul variabilelor aleatoare). Reamintim cƒÉ fiind datƒÉ matricea \(\boldsymbol Z = \left(Z_{ij}\right)_{i,j}\) unde \(Z_{ij}\), \(1\leq i\leq m\), \(1\leq j\leq k\) sunt variabile aleatoare de medie \(\mathbb{E}[Z_{ij}]\), media matricei \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Z]\) este definitƒÉ ca matricea mediilor \(\left(\mathbb{E}[Z_{ij}]\right)_{i,j}\). √én plus dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{l,m}(\mathbb{R})\), \(\boldsymbol B\in\mathcal{M}_{k,q}(\mathbb{R})\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol C\in\mathcal{M}_{l,q}(\mathbb{R})\) sunt trei matrice cu coeficien»õi constan»õi atunci

\[ \mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Z\boldsymbol B + \boldsymbol C\right] = \boldsymbol A\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Z]\boldsymbol B + \boldsymbol C. \]

√én mod similar, dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Z\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol T\) sunt doi vectori aleatori de dimensiune \(m\times 1\) »ôi respectiv \(k\times 1\) atunci covarian»õa acestora este definitƒÉ prin \(Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol T) = \left(Cov(Z_i, T_j)\right)_{i,j}\) »ôi se poate verifica rela»õia

\[ Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol T) = \mathbb{E}\left[\left(\boldsymbol Z - \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Z]\right)\left(\boldsymbol T - \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol T]\right)^\intercal\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol Z\boldsymbol T^\intercal\right] - \mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol Z\right]\mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol T\right]^\intercal = Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol Z)^\intercal. \]

√én particular pentru \(\boldsymbol T = \boldsymbol Z\) avem matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(Var(\boldsymbol Z) = Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol Z)\) care, √Æn conformitate cu rela»õia de mai sus, este egalƒÉ cu

\[ Var(\boldsymbol Z) = \mathbb{E}\left[\left(\boldsymbol Z - \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Z]\right)\left(\boldsymbol Z - \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Z]\right)^\intercal\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol Z\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\right] - \mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol Z\right]\mathbb{E}\left[\boldsymbol Z\right]^\intercal. \]

Un calcul direct aratƒÉ cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{l,m}(\mathbb{R})\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol B\in\mathcal{M}_{q, k}(\mathbb{R})\) sunt douƒÉ matrice cu coeficien»õi constan»õi atunci

\[ Cov\left(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol B\boldsymbol T\right) = \boldsymbol A Cov\left(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol T\right)\boldsymbol B^\intercal \]

iar atunci c√¢nd \(\boldsymbol T = \boldsymbol Z\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol A = \boldsymbol B\) gƒÉsim cƒÉ \(Var(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Z) = \boldsymbol A Var(\boldsymbol Z)\boldsymbol A^\intercal\). De asemenea, dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Z\), \(\boldsymbol T\), \(\boldsymbol U\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol V\) sunt vectori aleatori de dimensiune \(m\times 1\) iar \(a,b,c,d\in\mathbb{R}\) sunt constante reale atunci

\[ Cov(a\boldsymbol Z + b\boldsymbol T, c\boldsymbol U + d\boldsymbol V) = ac Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol U) + ad Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol V) + bc Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol U) + bd Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol V) \]

»ôi respectiv

\[ Var(a\boldsymbol Z + b\boldsymbol T) = a^2 Var(\boldsymbol Z) + ab\left(Cov(\boldsymbol Z, \boldsymbol T) + Cov(\boldsymbol T, \boldsymbol Z)\right) + b^2 Var(\boldsymbol T). \]

Pentru a verifica nedeplasarea estimatorului \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate sƒÉ notƒÉm cƒÉ, √Æn contextul ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_1\), acesta este \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\). Astfel putem scrie

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \mathbb{E}\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\right] = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon] \]

»ôi cum \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon] = 0\) conform \(\mathcal{H}_2\) deducem cƒÉ

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X}_{ = I_{p+1}}\boldsymbol \beta + \underbrace{\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon]}_{=0} = \boldsymbol \beta. \]

Pentru matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ avem

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) &= Var\left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\right) = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right) \left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal\right)^\intercal \\ &= (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right) \boldsymbol X (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \end{align*}\]

unde √Æn ultima egalitate am »õinut cont de simetria matricei \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\): \(\left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right)^\intercal = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\). Din modelul de regresie avem cƒÉ \(Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right) = Var\left(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon\right) = Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon)\) »ôi din ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_2\) avem \(Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n\) prin urmare

\[ Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \underbrace{Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right)}_{= \sigma^2 I_n} \boldsymbol X (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \sigma^2 \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X}_{= I_{p+1}} (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}. \]

Estimatorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate este estimatorul liniar, nedeplasat de varian»õƒÉ minimalƒÉ (BLUE).

Rezultatul acestui exerci»õiu este cunoscut »ôi sub denumirea de Teorema Gauss-Markov (a se vedea (Faraway 2015, Capitolul 2)). Pentru a putea solu»õiona acest exerci»õiu trebuie pentru √Ænceput sƒÉ remarcƒÉm c√¢teva aspecte: √Æn primul r√¢nd, liniaritatea estimatorului se referƒÉ la liniaritatea √Æn raport cu \(\boldsymbol Y\), adicƒÉ vorbim de clasa estimatorilor de forma \(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y\) unde \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{p+1, n}(\mathbb{R]})\); √Æn al doilea r√¢nd pentru a determina varian»õa minimalƒÉ avem nevoie de o rela»õie par»õialƒÉ de ordine pe mul»õimea matricelor simetrice, ori o asemenea rela»õie existƒÉ »ôi spune cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol S_1\leq \boldsymbol S_2\) atunci c√¢nd \(\boldsymbol S = \boldsymbol S_2 - \boldsymbol S_1\) este pozitiv definitƒÉ (valorile proprii ale lui \(\boldsymbol S\) sunt \(\geq 0\)), cu alte cuvinte \(\boldsymbol S_1\leq \boldsymbol S_2\) dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol S_1\boldsymbol x\leq \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol S_2\boldsymbol x\) pentru orice \(\boldsymbol x\).

√én acest context, cum \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un estimator nedeplasat (conform exerci»õiului anterior) »ôi liniar deoarece \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{A} \boldsymbol Y\), consider√¢nd \(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}\) un alt estimator liniar »ôi nedeplasat pentru \(\boldsymbol \beta\) vrem sƒÉ arƒÉtƒÉm cƒÉ \(Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta})\geq Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})\). Avem, conform proprietƒÉ»õilor matricei de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ de mai sus, descompunerea

\[ Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}) = Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} + \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) + Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) + Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) + Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}). \]

Cum matricele de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ sunt pozitiv semidefinite (pentru \(\boldsymbol a\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) avem \(\boldsymbol a^\intercal Var(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta})\boldsymbol a = Var(\boldsymbol a^\intercal\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta})\geq 0\), deoarece varian»õa este pozitivƒÉ) este suficient sƒÉ arƒÉtƒÉm cƒÉ \(Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = 0\). Liniaritatea estimatorului \(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}\) implicƒÉ \(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y\) iar nedeplasarea acestuia, \(\mathbb{E}[\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol \beta\) pentru orice \(\boldsymbol \beta\), conduce la \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta = \boldsymbol \beta\) pentru orice \(\boldsymbol \beta\) de unde \(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol X = I_{p+1}\).

√én final avem

\[\begin{align*} Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta} - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) &= Cov(\tilde{\boldsymbol \beta}, \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = Cov\left(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y, (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol Y\right) - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})\\ &= \boldsymbol A Cov\left(\boldsymbol Y, \boldsymbol Y\right) \left((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol X^\intercal\right)^\intercal - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = \boldsymbol A \underbrace{Var\left(\boldsymbol Y\right)}_{=\sigma^2 I_n}\boldsymbol X (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} - \underbrace{Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})}_{=\sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}}\\ &= \sigma^2\underbrace{\boldsymbol A \boldsymbol X}_{= I_{p+1}} (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} - \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = 0. \end{align*}\]

Fie \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} = \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) vectorul valorilor reziduale. ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2\) au loc rela»õiile

  1. \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}] = 0\) »ôi \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}\)
  2. \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol Y}] = \boldsymbol X \boldsymbol\beta\) »ôi \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}) = \sigma^2 P_{X}\)
  3. \(Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \hat{\boldsymbol Y}) = 0\)
  1. Am vƒÉzut cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = P_X\boldsymbol Y\) prin urmare

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} = (\hat{\varepsilon}_1,\ldots, \hat{\varepsilon}_n)^\intercal = \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y} = (I - P_X)\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon) = P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol\varepsilon \]

deoarece \(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\in\mathcal{M}(X)\), deci \(P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta = 0\). Astfel

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}] = \mathbb{E}[P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol\varepsilon] = P_{X^\perp} \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol\varepsilon] = 0 \] iar, »õin√¢nd seama de proprietatea de simetrie \(P_{X^\perp}^\intercal = P_{X^\perp}\) »ôi idempoten»õƒÉ \(P_{X^\perp}^2 = P_{X^\perp}\) a matricei de proiec»õie,

\[ Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = Var(P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol\varepsilon) = P_{X^\perp} Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon) P_{X^\perp}^\intercal = P_{X^\perp} \underbrace{Var(\boldsymbol\varepsilon)}_{=\sigma^2 I_n} P_{X^\perp} = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}^2 = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}. \]

  1. Din nedeplasarea lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) »ôi defini»õia lui \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) avem

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol Y}] = \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol X\mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}] = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta. \]

√én mod similar

\[ Var(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}) = Var(\boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) = \boldsymbol X \underbrace{Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta})}_{=\sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}}\boldsymbol X^\intercal = \sigma^2\underbrace{\boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{=P_X} = \sigma^2 P_X. \]

  1. Pentru a calcula \(Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \hat{\boldsymbol Y})\) folosim \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}\) »ôi \(Var(\boldsymbol Y) = Var(\boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n\) »ôi avem

\[\begin{align*} Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \hat{\boldsymbol Y}) &= Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \boldsymbol Y) - Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}) = Cov(P_{X^\perp} \boldsymbol Y, \boldsymbol Y) - \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} \\ &= P_{X^\perp}Var(\boldsymbol Y) P_{X^\perp}^\intercal - \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} = \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} - \sigma^2 P_{X^\perp} = 0. \end{align*}\]

Statistica \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\).

Ca sƒÉ arƒÉtƒÉm cƒÉ \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}\) este un estimator nedeplasat pentru \(\sigma^2\) trebuie sƒÉ calculƒÉm \(\mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right]\). Cum \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\) este un scalar atunci \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2 = \mathrm{Tr}(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2)\) (este egal cu urma sa) prin urmare

\[ \mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\mathrm{Tr}\left(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right)\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\mathrm{Tr}\left(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\right)\right] \]

»ôi cum pentru orice matrice \(\boldsymbol A\) urma verificƒÉ \(\mathrm{Tr}(\boldsymbol A^\intercal \boldsymbol A) = \mathrm{Tr}(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol A^\intercal) = \sum_{i,j}a_{ij}^2\) avem (\(\mathbb{E}\left[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\right] = 0\))

\[\begin{align*} \mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right] &= \mathbb{E}\left[\mathrm{Tr}\left(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\right)\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\mathrm{Tr}\left(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}^\intercal\right)\right] = \mathrm{Tr}\left(\mathbb{E}\left[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}^\intercal\right]\right) = \mathrm{Tr}\left(\mathbb{E}\left[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon} \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}^\intercal\right] - \mathbb{E}\left[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\right]\mathbb{E}\left[\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\right]^\intercal\right) \\ &= \mathrm{Tr}\left(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon})\right) = \mathrm{Tr}\left(\sigma^2 P_{X^\perp}\right) = \sigma^2 \mathrm{Tr}\left( P_{X^\perp}\right). \end{align*}\]

Cum \(P_{X^\perp} = I - P_{X}\) este matrice de proiec»õie avem cƒÉ \(\mathrm{Tr}\left( P_{X^\perp}\right) = \textrm{rang}\left( P_{X^\perp}\right) = n - (p+1)\) (urma matricei de proiec»õie este egalƒÉ cu dimensiunea spa»õiului pe care proiectƒÉm) prin urmare

\[ \mathbb{E}\left[\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2\right] = \sigma^2 \left[n - (p+1)\right] \]

de unde \(\mathbb{E}\left[\hat{\sigma}^2\right] = \mathbb{E}\left[\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}\right] = \sigma^2\).

Folosind estimatorul \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) putem construi un estimator \(\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2\) pentru varian»õa \(Var(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}) = \sigma^2 (\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\):

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}}^2 = \hat{\sigma}^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}. \]

√én particular, un estimator pentru abaterea standard a estimatorului coeficientului \(\beta_j\), \(\hat{\beta}_j\), este dat de elementul \(j+1\) de pe diagonala matricii \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\):

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j} = \hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}},\quad j = 0,1,\ldots,p. \]

Fie \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouƒÉ observa»õie »ôi considerƒÉm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ne propunem sƒÉ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\), \(Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\) »ôi \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\).

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ eroare de predic»õie \(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1} = y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) verificƒÉ proprietƒÉ»õile

  1. \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}] = 0\)

  2. \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right)\)
  1. Cum \(\mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\) »ôi »õin√¢nd cont de nedeplasarea estimatorului \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) avem

\[ \mathbb{E}[\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}] = \mathbb{E}[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}] = \mathbb{E}\left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1}}_{y_{n+1}} - \underbrace{\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}}_{\hat{y}_{n+1}}\right] \]

de unde \(\mathbb{E}[\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}] = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \mathbb{E}[\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}]\right) + \mathbb{E}[\varepsilon_{n+1}] = 0\).

Cum \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) depinde doar de variabilele \(\{\varepsilon_1,\ldots,\varepsilon_n\}\) iar \(Cov(\varepsilon_{n+1}, \varepsilon_i)=0\) pentru \(i = 1,\ldots,n\) deducem cƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) &= Var\left(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\right) = Var\left(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}\right) \\ &= Var\left(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right)\right) + Var(\varepsilon_{n+1}) = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal Var(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) \boldsymbol x_{n+1} + \sigma^2\\ &= \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal Var(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}) \boldsymbol x_{n+1} + \sigma^2 = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1} \boldsymbol x_{n+1} + \sigma^2\\ &= \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right). \end{align*}\]

Fie modelul de regresie \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) unde matricea de design se scrie

\[ \boldsymbol {X}=\begin{pmatrix} 1 & x_{11} & \cdots & x_{1p}\\ \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots\\ 1 & x_{n1} & \cdots & x_{np} \end{pmatrix}_{n\times(p+1)} = \left[\underbrace{\boldsymbol X_0}_{\mathbf{1} = (1,\cdots,1)}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right] = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol Z\right] \]

cu \(\boldsymbol Z\) matricea de dimensiune \(n\times p\) formatƒÉ din coloanele \(\{\boldsymbol X_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol X_p\}\). √én contextul exerci»õiului anterior, fie \(\boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal = (x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouƒÉ observa»õie »ôi considerƒÉm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal)\). ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ varian»õa erorii de predic»õie este

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{1}{n}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\right] \]

unde \(\boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\) este o matrice simetricƒÉ »ôi pozitiv definitƒÉ atunci c√¢nd \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este inversabilƒÉ iar \(\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = (\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1, \ldots, \bar{\boldsymbol x}_p)\) cu \(\bar{\boldsymbol x}_j = \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_{ij}\).

Pentru √Ænceput sƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) se scrie sub forma

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X &= \begin{bmatrix}\mathbf{1}^\intercal \\ \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal \\ \vdots \\ \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots &\boldsymbol X_p\end{bmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\underbrace{\mathbf{1}^\intercal\mathbf{1}}_{=n} & \underbrace{\mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1}_{=n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1} & \cdots & \underbrace{\mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol X_p}_{=n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_p}\\ \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\\ \cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots \\ \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}n & n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1 & \cdots & n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_p\\ n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_1 & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_1^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\\ \cdots & \cdots & \cdots & \cdots\\ n\bar{\boldsymbol x}_p & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal\boldsymbol X_1 & \cdots & \boldsymbol X_p^\intercal \boldsymbol X_p\end{pmatrix}\\ &= \begin{pmatrix}n & n\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\\ n\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z\end{pmatrix} = n\begin{pmatrix}1 & \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\\ \bar{\boldsymbol x} & \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z\end{pmatrix}. \end{align*}\]

Reamintim, e.g.¬†(Henderson and Searle 1981), cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol F\) este o matrice pƒÉtratƒÉ inversabilƒÉ care se scrie sub formƒÉ de bloc de patru submatrice

\[ \boldsymbol F = \begin{pmatrix}\boldsymbol A & \boldsymbol B\\ \boldsymbol C & \boldsymbol D\end{pmatrix} \]

cu \(\boldsymbol A\) inversabilƒÉ atunci matricea \(\boldsymbol Q = \boldsymbol D - \boldsymbol C \boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B\) este inversabilƒÉ iar inversa matricii \(\boldsymbol F\) este

\[ \boldsymbol F^{-1} = \begin{pmatrix}\boldsymbol A^{-1} + \boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol C\boldsymbol A^{-1} & -\boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B\boldsymbol Q\\ -\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol C\boldsymbol A^{-1} & \boldsymbol Q\end{pmatrix}. \]

√én cazul problemei noastre avem \(\boldsymbol A = 1\), \(\boldsymbol B = \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\), \(\boldsymbol C = \bar{\boldsymbol x}\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol D = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z\) prin urmare

\[ \boldsymbol Q = \boldsymbol D - \boldsymbol C \boldsymbol A^{-1}\boldsymbol B = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = \boldsymbol \Gamma \]

iar

\[ \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right)^{-1} = \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 & \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\\ \bar{\boldsymbol x} & \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal \boldsymbol Z\end{pmatrix}^{-1} = \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & -\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\\ -\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\end{pmatrix}. \] Dat fiind \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal)\) am vƒÉzut √Æn exerci»õiul precedent cƒÉ varian»õa erorii de predic»õie este datƒÉ de formula

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right). \]

»öin√¢nd cont de scrierea sub formƒÉ de blocuri a matricei \(\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right)^{-1}\) gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1} &= \begin{pmatrix}1 & \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\end{pmatrix} \frac{1}{n}\begin{pmatrix}1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & -\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\\ -\boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} & \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}\end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix}1\\ \boldsymbol z_{n+1}\end{pmatrix} \\ &= \frac{1}{n}\left(1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} + \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1}\right). \end{align*}\]

Not√¢nd cu \(\boldsymbol Z_c\) matricea (centratƒÉ) cu coloanele \(\boldsymbol X_j - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_j\mathbf{1}\), \(j = 1,\ldots,p\) putem observa cƒÉ

\[ \boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z^\intercal\boldsymbol Z - \bar{\boldsymbol x}\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c \]

prin urmare \(\boldsymbol \Gamma = \boldsymbol \Gamma^\intercal\), deci \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este simetricƒÉ. Astfel, folosind faptul cƒÉ un scalar este egal cu transpusul sƒÉu, avem

\[ \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} = \left(\boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal \boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x}\right)^\intercal = \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} \]

ceea ce conduce la

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1} &= \frac{1}{n}\left(1 + \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\bar{\boldsymbol x} - 2\bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1} + \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol\Gamma^{-1}\boldsymbol z_{n+1}\right) \\ &= \frac{1}{n}\left[1 + (\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\right] \end{align*}\]

de unde gƒÉsim

\[ Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left[1 + \frac{1}{n} + \frac{1}{n}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\right]. \]

Mai mult, sƒÉ remarcƒÉm cƒÉ dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) este inversabilƒÉ atunci matricea \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este pozitiv definitƒÉ. √éntr-adevƒÉr am vƒÉzut cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol \Gamma = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c\) iar pentru \(\boldsymbol u \in\mathbb{R}^p\) putem scrie

\[ \boldsymbol u^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma\boldsymbol u = \frac{1}{n}\boldsymbol u^\intercal \boldsymbol Z_c^\intercal\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u = \frac{1}{n}\lVert\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u\rVert^2 \geq 0 \]

deci \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este pozitiv semidefinitƒÉ. Avem egalitate \(\frac{1}{n}\lVert\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u\rVert^2 = 0\) atunci c√¢nd \(\boldsymbol Z_c \boldsymbol u = 0\) sau, altfel spus, atunci c√¢nd

\[ u_1(\boldsymbol X_1 - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_1\mathbf{1}) + \cdots + u_p(\boldsymbol X_p - \bar{\boldsymbol x}_p\mathbf{1}) = 0 \iff \sum_{j=1}^{n}u_j\boldsymbol X_j = \left(\sum_{j=1}^{n}u_j\bar{\boldsymbol x}_j\right)\mathbf{1}. \]

AceastƒÉ ultimƒÉ rela»õie ne spune cƒÉ prima coloanƒÉ a lui \(\boldsymbol X\) se scrie ca o combina»õie liniarƒÉ de celelalte, ceea ce √ÆnseamnƒÉ cƒÉ \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X)\leq p\) de unde concluzionƒÉm cƒÉ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\) nu este inversabilƒÉ.
