Cum \(\boldsymbol \Gamma\) este simetricƒÉ »ôi pozitiv definitƒÉ deducem cƒÉ \((\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})^\intercal \boldsymbol \Gamma^{-1}(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} - \bar{\boldsymbol x})\geq 0\), cu egalitate dacƒÉ »ôi numai dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol z_{n+1} = \bar{\boldsymbol x}\), adicƒÉ \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, \boldsymbol z_{n+1}^\intercal) = (1, \bar{\boldsymbol x}^\intercal)\). √én acest caz \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1+\frac{1}{n}\right)\), rezultat care generalizeazƒÉ rezultatul corespunzƒÉtor de la regresia liniarƒÉ simplƒÉ: trebuie sƒÉ ne plasƒÉm √Æn centrul norului de puncte ale variabilelor explicative pentru a prezice variabila rƒÉspuns cu mai multƒÉ precizie.

2.3 InterpretƒÉri geometrice - coeficientul de determinare

Fie modelul de regresie \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) √Æn care \(\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul rƒÉspuns, \(\boldsymbol X = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\in\mathcal{M}_{n, p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) este matricea de design (\(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\)), \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) este vectorul parametrilor »ôi \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul erorilor. NotƒÉm cu \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) subspa»õiul generat de coloanele matricii \(\boldsymbol X\), cu \(\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) subspa»õiul ortogonal, cu \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi cu \(\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon} = \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\in\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) vectorul reziduurilor.

Conform figurii de mai sus observƒÉm cƒÉ putem aplica Teorema lui Pitagora √Æn triunghiul albastru »ôi ob»õinem descompunerea

\[ \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 = \lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 + \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2 \]

unde

  • \(SS_{T} = \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2\) se nume»ôte suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice totale (varia»õia totalƒÉ)

  • \(SS_{reg} = \lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2\) se nume»ôte suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice de regresie (varia»õia explicatƒÉ de model)

  • \(RSS = \lVert \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2\) se nume»ôte suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice reziduale (varia»õia rezidualƒÉ)

Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\) (√Æn R are denumirea de \(\texttt{Multiple R-Squared}\)) este definit prin

\[ R^2 = \cos^2(\theta) = \frac{\text{Varia»õia explicatƒÉ de model}}{\text{Varia»õia totalƒÉ}} = \frac{\lVert \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} \] »ôi ne dƒÉ propor»õia din variabilitatea lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) explicatƒÉ prin modelul de regresie. Cum \(R^2\) nu »õine cont de dimensiunea spa»õiului \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) se define»ôte coeficientul de determinare ajustat \(R_a^2\) (√Æn R are denumirea de \(\texttt{Adjusted R-Squared}\)) prin

\[ R_a^2 = 1 - \frac{\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n-(p+1)}}{\frac{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2}{n-1}} = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2}. \]

Ajustarea corespunde la √ÆmpƒÉr»õirea normelor la pƒÉtrat cu dimensiunea subspa»õiului din care fac parte vectorii.

Ne propunem sƒÉ determinƒÉm evolu»õia unei variabile rƒÉspuns \(y_i\) √Æn func»õie de douƒÉ variabile explicative \(x_i\) »ôi \(z_i\). Fie \(\boldsymbol X = (\mathbf{1}, \boldsymbol x, \boldsymbol z)\) matricea de design.

  1. Am ob»õinut rezultatele urmƒÉtoare

\[ \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \begin{pmatrix}25 & 0 & 0\\ ? & 9.3 & 5.4\\ ? & ? & 12.7\end{pmatrix} \]

  1. Determina»õi valorile care lipsesc (?).

  2. C√¢t este \(n\) ?

  3. Calcula»õi coeficientul de corela»õie dintre \(\boldsymbol x\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol z\).

  1. Modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) √Æn func»õie de \(\mathbf{1}, \boldsymbol x, \boldsymbol z\) este

\[ \boldsymbol Y = -1.6\boldsymbol 1 + 0.61 \boldsymbol x + 0.46 \boldsymbol z + \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}, \quad \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2 = 0.3 \]

  1. Determina»õi \(\bar{\boldsymbol y}\).

  2. Calcula»õi suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice de regresie \(SS_{reg}\), suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice totale \(SS_T\), coeficientul de determinare »ôi coeficientul de determinare ajustat.

    1. Pentru a determina cele trei valori care lipsesc sƒÉ notƒÉm cƒÉ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\) este simetricƒÉ, prin urmare \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)^\intercal\) de unde

\[ \begin{pmatrix}25 & 0 & 0\\ ? & 9.3 & 5.4\\ ? & ? & 12.7\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}25 & ? & ?\\ 0 & 9.3 & ?\\ 0 & 5.4 & 12.7\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce conduce la valorile \(0, 0, 5.4\).

  1. Pentru a determina valoarea lui \(n\) sƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ

\[ \boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \begin{pmatrix}\mathbf{1}^\intercal \\ \boldsymbol x^\intercal\\ \boldsymbol z^\intercal\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol z\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}\mathbf{1}^\intercal \mathbf{1} & \mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \mathbf{1}^\intercal\boldsymbol z \\ \boldsymbol x^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol z\\ \boldsymbol z^\intercal\mathbf{1} & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol z\end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix}n & n\bar x & n\bar z \\ n\bar x & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol z\\ n\bar z & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol x & \boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol z\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce aratƒÉ cƒÉ \(n = \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{1,1} = 25\).

  1. Coeficientul de corela»õie dintre \(\boldsymbol x\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol z\) este dat de

\[ r_{\boldsymbol x,\boldsymbol z} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)(z_i - \bar z)}{\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(x_i - \bar x)^2}\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(z_i - \bar z)^2}} \]

»ôi cum, din punctul anterior, \(\bar x = \frac{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{1,2}}{n} = 0\) »ôi \(\bar z = \frac{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{1,3}}{n} = 0\) deci

\[ r_{\boldsymbol x,\boldsymbol z} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_iz_i}{\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}x_i^2}\sqrt{\sum_{i = 1}^{n}z_i^2}} = \frac{\boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol z}{\sqrt{\boldsymbol x^\intercal\boldsymbol x}\sqrt{\boldsymbol z^\intercal\boldsymbol z}} = \frac{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,3}}{\sqrt{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,2}}\sqrt{\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{3,3}}} = \frac{5.4}{\sqrt{9.3}\sqrt{12.7}}\approx 0.5 \]

    1. Avem modelul

\[ y_i = -1.6 + 0.61 x_i + 0.46 z_i + \hat{\varepsilon}_i \]

care prin sumare devine

\[ \bar y = -1.6 + 0.61 \bar x + 0.46 \bar z + \frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i. \]

Cum \(\mathbf{1}\) apar»õine modelului, deci \(\mathbf{1}\in\mathcal{M}(\boldsymbol X)\) »ôi »õin√¢nd cont de faptul cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\in\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) deducem cƒÉ \(\langle\mathbf{1}, \hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rangle = 0\) sau \(\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i = 0\). Astfel

\[ \bar y = -1.6 + 0.61 \underbrace{\bar x}_{=0} + 0.46 \underbrace{\bar z}_{= 0} + \underbrace{\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i}_{=0} = -1.6. \]

  1. Avem cƒÉ suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice explicate de model este datƒÉ de

\[ SS_{reg} = \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}(\hat{y}_i - \bar y)^2 = \sum_{i=1}^{n}(0.61 x_i + 0.46 z_i)^2 \]

adicƒÉ

\[\begin{align*} SS_{reg} &= \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2 = 0.61^2\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_i^2 + 2\times 0.61\times 0.46\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_iz_i + 0.46^2\sum_{i=1}^{n}z_i^2\\ &= 0.61^2\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,2} + 2\times 0.61\times 0.46\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{2,3} + 0.46^2\left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\right)_{3,3} = 9.18. \end{align*}\]

Suma abaterilor pƒÉtratice totale se determinƒÉ folosind formula de descompunere a varian»õei:

\[ \underbrace{SS_T}_{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = \underbrace{SS_{reg}}_{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \bar y\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} + \underbrace{RSS}_{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2} = 9.18 + 0.3 = 9.48. \]

Coeficientul de determinare \(R^2\) este

\[ R^2 = \frac{SS_{reg}}{SS_T} = \frac{9.18}{9.48}\approx 0.968 \]

ceea ce aratƒÉ cƒÉ aproximativ \(97\%\) din variabilitatea datelor este explicatƒÉ de modelul de regresie iar coeficientul de determinare ajustat este

\[ R_1^2 = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - \bar{\boldsymbol y}\mathbf{1}\rVert^2} = 1 - \frac{n-1}{n-(p+1)}\left(1 - R^2\right) = 1 - \frac{25 - 1}{25 - (2 + 1)}(1-0.968)\approx 0.965 \]

ceea ce verificƒÉ rela»õia generalƒÉ \(R_a^2<R^2\).

Fie \(\boldsymbol Z\in\mathcal{M}_{n,q}(\mathbb{R})\) o matrice de rang \(q\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol X\in\mathcal{M}_{n,p}(\mathbb{R})\) o matrice de rang \(p\), \(p>q\), compusƒÉ din cei \(q\) vectori coloanƒÉ ai lui \(\boldsymbol Z\) »ôi din al»õi \(p-q\) vectori liniar independen»õi. ConsiderƒÉm modelele urmƒÉtoare:

\[\begin{align*} \boldsymbol Y &= \boldsymbol Z\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon,\\ \boldsymbol Y &= \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \gamma + \boldsymbol\eta \end{align*}\]

Presupunem, pentru simplitate, cƒÉ niciun model nu con»õine termenul liber (constanta). NotƒÉm cu \(P_X\) »ôi \(P_Z\) matricele de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe subspa»õiile \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi respectiv \(\mathcal{M}(Z)\), generate de coloanele lui \(\boldsymbol X\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol Z\). De asemenea notƒÉm cu \(P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\) matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\cap \mathcal{M}(Z)^\perp\), subspa»õiul ortogonal al lui \(\mathcal{M}(Z)\) din \(\mathcal{M}(X)\), astfel

\[ \mathbb{R}^n = \mathcal{M}(X) \oplus \mathcal{M}(X)^\perp = \left(\mathcal{M}(Z) \oplus \left(\mathcal{M}(X)\cap \mathcal{M}(Z)^\perp\right) \right) \oplus \mathcal{M}(X)^\perp \]

  1. Exprima»õi \(\lVert P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2\) √Æn func»õie de \(\lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2\) »ôi de \(\lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2\).

  2. Compara»õi coeficien»õii de determinare a celor douƒÉ modele, \(R_Z^2\) »ôi \(R_X^2\).

Acest exerci»õiu face referire la modele imbricate - nested models.

  1. Deoarece \(\mathcal{M}(\boldsymbol Z)\subset\mathcal{M}(\boldsymbol X)\) »ôi aplic√¢nd teorema celor trei perpendiculare2 avem, vezi figura de mai jos,

\[\begin{align*} \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_p &= P_X\boldsymbol Y = (\underbrace{P_Z + P_{Z^\perp}}_{I}) P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_Z P_X \boldsymbol Y + P_{Z^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y\\ &= P_X\boldsymbol Y + P_{X\cap Z^\perp} \boldsymbol Y = \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_q + P_{X\cap Z^\perp} \boldsymbol Y \end{align*}\]

»ôi din Teorema lui Pitagora (vezi triunghiul ro»ôu) deducem cƒÉ

\[ \lVert P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2. \]

  1. DacƒÉ modelul nu are termenul liber (constanta) atunci coeficientul de determinare este definit prin \(R_X^2 = \frac{\lVert P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}\) prin urmare

\[ R_X^2 = \frac{\lVert P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2} = \frac{\lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2} = R_Z^2 + \frac{\lVert P_{X\cap Z^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}\geq R_Z^2. \]

Rezultatul de mai sus se generalizeazƒÉ »ôi √Æn cazul modelelor imbricate care con»õin termenul constant »ôi ne spune aratƒÉ cƒÉ modelul mai mare are un coeficient de determinare superior modelului mai mic. Altfel spus, dacƒÉ la un model dat adƒÉugƒÉm una sau mai multe variabile explicative ameliorƒÉm variabilitatea explicatƒÉ de model, chiar dacƒÉ variabilele explicative suplimentare nu sunt pertinente! √én acest caz este de preferat coeficientul de determinare ajustat.

ConsiderƒÉm modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon \]

unde \(\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\), \(\boldsymbol X \in\mathcal{M}_{n, p}(\mathbb{R})\) este o matrice compusƒÉ din \(p\) vectori ortogonali, \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p}\) iar \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\in\mathbb{R}^n\). Fie \(\boldsymbol Z\) matricea formatƒÉ din primele \(q\) coloane ale lui \(\boldsymbol X\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol U\) matricea formatƒÉ din ultimele \(p-q\) coloane ale lui \(\boldsymbol X\). Prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate ob»õinem

\[\begin{align*} \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_X &= \hat{\beta}_1^X \boldsymbol X_1 + \cdots + \hat{\beta}_p^X \boldsymbol X_p\\ \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_Z &= \hat{\beta}_1^Z \boldsymbol X_1 + \cdots + \hat{\beta}_q^Z \boldsymbol X_q\\ \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_U &= \hat{\beta}_{q+1}^U \boldsymbol X_{q+1} + \cdots + \hat{\beta}_p^U \boldsymbol X_p \end{align*}\]

  1. ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ \(\lVert P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_U\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2\).
  2. Pentru \(i\in\{1,2,\ldots,p\}\) dat, arƒÉta»õi cƒÉ \(\hat{\beta}_i^X = \hat{\beta}_i^Z\) dacƒÉ \(i\leq q\) »ôi \(\hat{\beta}_i^X = \hat{\beta}_i^U\) altfel.
  1. Cum \(P_Z + P_{Z^\perp} = I\) putem scrie

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_X = P_X\boldsymbol Y = (P_Z + P_{Z^\perp})P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_ZP_X\boldsymbol Y + P_{Z^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y, \]

»ôi din \(P_ZP_X = P_{Z\cap X} = P_Z\) gƒÉsim cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_X = P_Z\boldsymbol Y + P_{Z^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y\). De asemenea, sƒÉ notƒÉm cƒÉ \(P_{Z^\perp}P_X = P_{Z^\perp\cap X}\) »ôi »õin√¢nd cont de faptul cƒÉ matricea \(\boldsymbol X\) are coloanele ortogonale avem \(P_{Z^\perp\cap X} = P_U\) (√Æn fapt ortogonalitatea coloanelor lui \(\boldsymbol X\) implicƒÉ \(\mathcal{M}(X) = \mathcal{M}(Z)\overset{\perp}{\oplus}\mathcal{M}(U)\), sumƒÉ directƒÉ de spa»õii ortogonale). Prin urmare ob»õinem descompunerea ortogonalƒÉ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_X = P_Z\boldsymbol Y + P_U\boldsymbol Y = \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_Z + \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_U \]

»ôi din Teorema lui Pitagora avem

\[ \lVert P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert P_Z\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_U\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2. \]

  1. Vom arƒÉta rela»õia pentru \(i\leq q\), cazul general fiind analog. Din formula generalƒÉ avem cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}^X\) este

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}^X = \left(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X\right)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y \]

»ôi cum coloanele lui \(\boldsymbol X\) sunt ortogonale deducem cƒÉ matricea \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X\) este o matrice diagonalƒÉ, \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X = \mathrm{diag}\left(\lVert\boldsymbol X_1\rVert^2, \ldots, \lVert\boldsymbol X_p\rVert^2\right)\). Not√¢nd de asemenea cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y\) este un vector coloanƒÉ cu elemente de tipul \(\langle\boldsymbol X_i, \boldsymbol Y\rangle\), deducem cƒÉ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}^X = \begin{pmatrix}\frac{\langle\boldsymbol X_1, \boldsymbol Y\rangle}{\lVert\boldsymbol X_1\rVert^2} & \cdots & \frac{\langle\boldsymbol X_p, \boldsymbol Y\rangle}{\lVert\boldsymbol X_p\rVert^2}\end{pmatrix}^\intercal, \] prin urmare \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_i^X = \frac{\langle\boldsymbol X_i, \boldsymbol Y\rangle}{\lVert\boldsymbol X_i\rVert^2}\). Pentru \(i\leq q\), coloana \(i\) a matricei \(\boldsymbol Z\) este \(\boldsymbol Z_i = \boldsymbol X_i\) »ôi aplic√¢nd ra»õionamentul anterior gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_i^Z = \frac{\langle\boldsymbol Z_i, \boldsymbol Y\rangle}{\lVert\boldsymbol Z_i\rVert^2} = \frac{\langle\boldsymbol X_i, \boldsymbol Y\rangle}{\lVert\boldsymbol X_i\rVert^2} = \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_i^X. \]

Rezultatul exerci»õiului ne spune cƒÉ √Æn cazul √Æn care variabilele explicative sunt ortogonale, a efectua o regresie multiplƒÉ revine la a efectua \(p\) regresii simple.

2.4 Modelul (condi»õionat) normal

ConsiderƒÉm modelul de regresie \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) √Æn care \(\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul rƒÉspuns, \(\boldsymbol X = \left[\mathbf{1}|\boldsymbol X_1|\cdots|\boldsymbol X_p\right]\in\mathcal{M}_{n, p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) este matricea de design, \(\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\) este vectorul parametrilor »ôi \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este vectorul erorilor. P√¢nƒÉ acum, ipotezele modelului erau

\[ \begin{array}{ll} \mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\\ \mathcal{H}_2: \, \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon] = 0,\, Var(\boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \sigma^2 I_n \end{array} \]

√én aceastƒÉ sec»õiune ne propunem sƒÉ studiem proprietƒÉ»õile statistice ale modelului de regresie liniarƒÉ plas√¢ndu-ne √Æntr-un context parametric »ôi anume √Æn contextul modelului gaussian:

\[ \begin{array}{ll} \mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\\ \mathcal{H}_2': \, \boldsymbol \varepsilon \sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I_n) \end{array} \]

ObservƒÉm cƒÉ ipoteza \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) este un caz particular al ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2\) »ôi √Æn plus implicƒÉ faptul cƒÉ reziduurile sunt independente »ôi identic repartizate. Ipoteza de normalitate a erorilor ne permite sƒÉ scriem func»õia de verosimilitate, sƒÉ deducem reparti»õiile estimatorilor propu»ôi, sƒÉ construim intervale de √Æncredere »ôi sƒÉ testƒÉm ipoteze statistice.

ConsiderƒÉm modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon \]

sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) de mai sus. Determina»õi estimatorii de verosimilitate maximƒÉ pentru \(\boldsymbol \beta\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol\varepsilon\).

√éncepem prin a observa cƒÉ din modelul de regresie

\[ y_i = \boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta + \varepsilon_i \]

»ôi conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) avem \(\varepsilon_i\sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2)\) prin urmare \(y_i\sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2)\) »ôi √Æn plus \(y_i\) sunt variabile aleatoare independete deoarece \(\varepsilon_i\) sunt independente. Astfel func»õia de verosimilitate se scrie

\[\begin{align*} L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) &= \prod_{i = 1}^{n}f_{Y}(y_i) = \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta)^2} \\ &= \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2} \end{align*}\]

ceea ce conduce la logaritmul func»õiei de verosimilitate

\[ l(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \log L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = -\frac{n}{2}\log{2\pi\sigma^2} -\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2. \]

Vrem sƒÉ determinƒÉm

\[ (\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2) = \underset{(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2)\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}\times(0,\infty)}{\arg\max} l(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) \]

»ôi observƒÉm cƒÉ pentru \(\sigma^2\) fixat, a maximiza func»õia \(l(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)\) revine la a determina valoarea lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) care minimizeazƒÉ \(\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2\), aceasta ne fiind alta dec√¢t \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate. Astfel gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM} = \hat{\boldsymbol\beta} = (\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol{X}^\intercal \boldsymbol Y. \]

Pentru a determina \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2\) sƒÉ observƒÉm cƒÉ problema revine la a determina solu»õia ecua»õiei

\[ \frac{\partial l(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y)}{\partial \sigma^2} = -\frac{n}{2\sigma^2} + \frac{1}{2\sigma^4}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}\rVert^2 = 0 \]

care este \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}\rVert^2}{n}=\frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n}\). Compar√¢nd acest rezultat cu cel ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate observƒÉm cƒÉ

\[ \hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2 = \frac{n - (p+1)}{n}\hat{\sigma}^2, \]

deci estimatorul de verosimilitate maximƒÉ \(\hat{\sigma}_{VM}^2\) a lui \(\sigma^2\) est un estimator deplasat. √én cele ce urmeazƒÉ vom considera estimatorul nedeplasat \(\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\hat{\varepsilon}_i}{n - (p+1)}\) ca estimator al lui \(\sigma^2\).

2.4.1 Reparti»õiile estimatorilor, intervale »ôi regiuni de √Æncredere

√énainte de a investiga reparti»õiile estimatorilor \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) »ôi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) pentru modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ sub ipoteza de normalitate, sƒÉ reamintim c√¢teva no»õiuni legate de vectorii gaussieni (pentru mai multe detalii se poate consulta (Seber and Lee 2003, Capitolul 2) sau (Jacod and Protter 2003, Capitolul 16)).

Spunem cƒÉ un vector \(\boldsymbol Y = (Y_1,\ldots,Y_n)\in\mathbb{R}^n\) este un vector gaussian dacƒÉ toate combina»õiile liniare \(\sum_{i=1}^{n}a_iY_i\) sunt repartizate normal (posibil degenerat dacƒÉ to»õi coeficien»õii sunt nuli). Acest vector admite o medie \(\boldsymbol\mu = \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y]\) »ôi o matrice de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \mathbb{E}[(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)^\intercal]\) care caracterizeazƒÉ complet reparti»õia lui \(\boldsymbol Y\). √én acest caz notƒÉm \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\). Un vector gaussian \(\boldsymbol Y\) admite o densitate de reparti»õie \(f_{\boldsymbol Y}\) pe \(\mathbb{R}^n\) dacƒÉ »ôi numai dacƒÉ matricea sa de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) este inversabilƒÉ »ôi √Æn acest caz

\[ f_{\boldsymbol Y}(\boldsymbol y) = \frac{1}{(2\pi)^{\frac{n}{2}}\sqrt{\det{\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}}}} e^{-\frac{1}{2}(\boldsymbol y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol y - \boldsymbol \mu)} \]

√én cazul √Æn care matricea \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) nu este inversabilƒÉ √ÆnseamnƒÉ cƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Y\) ia valori √Æntr-un subspa»õiu de dimensiune \(n_0<n\) unde este repartizat ca un vector gaussian de dimensiune \(n_0\).

Figura de mai jos prezintƒÉ patru reparti»õii normale bivariate (\(n=2\)) \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\), cu \(\boldsymbol\mu = (\mu_1, \mu_2)^\intercal\) iar \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \begin{pmatrix}\sigma_{11} & \sigma_{12}\\ \sigma_{21} & \sigma_{22}\end{pmatrix}= \begin{pmatrix}\sigma_{1}^2 & \sigma_{12}\\ \sigma_{12} & \sigma_{2}^2\end{pmatrix}\), rotite cu unghiul \(\alpha\). √én acest caz densitatea de reparti»õie este

\[ f_{\boldsymbol Y}(y_1,y_2) = \frac{1}{2\pi\sigma_1\sigma_2\sqrt{1-\rho^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2(1-\rho^2)}\left[\left(\frac{y_1 - \mu_1}{\sigma_1}\right)^2 - 2\rho\left(\frac{y_1 - \mu_1}{\sigma_1}\right)\left(\frac{y_2 - \mu_2}{\sigma_2}\right) + \left(\frac{y_2 - \mu_2}{\sigma_2}\right)^2\right]} \]

unde \(\rho = \frac{\sigma_{12}}{\sigma_1\sigma_2}\) este coeficientul de corela»õie.

Una dintre proprietƒÉ»õile importante ale vectorilor gaussieni este stabilitatea prin transformƒÉri afine: dacƒÉ \(\boldsymbol A\in\mathcal{M}_{m,n}(\mathbb{R})\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol b\in\mathcal{M}_{m,1}(\mathbb{R})\) sunt respectiv o matrice »ôi un vector de scalari atunci

\[ \boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}) \Longrightarrow \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol Y + \boldsymbol b \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol A\boldsymbol\mu + \boldsymbol b, \boldsymbol A\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\boldsymbol A^\intercal) \]

De asemenea, plec√¢nd de la func»õia caracteristicƒÉ, se poate verifica proprietatea de independen»õƒÉ a componentelor unui vector gaussian care ne spune cƒÉ acestea sunt independente dacƒÉ »ôi numai dacƒÉ matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ este o matrice diagonalƒÉ.

Avem urmƒÉtorul rezultat care face legƒÉtura dintre reparti»õia normalƒÉ »ôi reparti»õia \(\chi^2\):

Fie \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y})\) un vector gaussian √Æn \(\mathbb{R}^n\). DacƒÉ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) este o matrice inversabilƒÉ atunci

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) \sim \chi_n^2 \]

reparti»õia \(\chi^2\) cu \(n\) grade de libertate.

Deoarece matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) este o matrice simetricƒÉ »ôi pozitiv definitƒÉ atunci din Teorema de descompunere spectralƒÉ ea se poate descompune sub forma \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\) unde \(\boldsymbol Q = [\boldsymbol v_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol v_n]\) este o matrice ortogonalƒÉ (\(\boldsymbol Q^\intercal = \boldsymbol Q^{-1}\)) formatƒÉ din vectorii proprii \(\boldsymbol v_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol v_n\) corespunzƒÉtori valorilor proprii \(\lambda_1,\ldots,\lambda_n\), iar \(\boldsymbol \Delta\) este matricea diagonalƒÉ \(\mathrm{diag}(\lambda_1,\ldots,\lambda_n)\). DacƒÉ notƒÉm cu \(\boldsymbol \Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}}\) matricea diagonalƒÉ de coeficien»õi diagonali \(\frac{1}{\sqrt{\lambda_1}},\ldots,\frac{1}{\sqrt{\lambda_n}}\) (aceste frac»õii existƒÉ deoarece pozitiv definirea matricei \(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}\) implicƒÉ faptul cƒÉ valorile proprii \(\lambda_i>0\), \(i = 1,\ldots,n\)) atunci

\[ \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta \boldsymbol Q^\intercal \Longrightarrow \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1} = \boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-1} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal = \left(\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\right)\left(\boldsymbol Q\boldsymbol\Delta^{-\frac{1}{2}} \boldsymbol Q^\intercal\right) = \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}. \]

Prin urmare gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) = \left(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\right)^\intercal\left(\Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\right) \]

»ôi cum vectorii gaussieni rƒÉm√¢n gaussieni »ôi prin aplicarea unor transformƒÉri afine (vezi rezultatul de mai sus) avem cƒÉ

\[ \boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}) \Longrightarrow \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) \sim\mathcal{N}(0, I_n). \]

Astfel vectorul \(\boldsymbol V = [\boldsymbol V_1,\ldots,\boldsymbol V_n]^\intercal = \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-\frac{1}{2}}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)\), care nu este altceva dec√¢t vectorul \(\boldsymbol Y\) centrat »ôi redus, este gaussian standard (\(\boldsymbol V_j\sim\mathcal{N}(0,1)\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol V_i\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol V_j\) sunt independente) »ôi

\[ (\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu)^\intercal \Sigma_{\boldsymbol Y}^{-1}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol \mu) = \lVert \boldsymbol V\rVert^2 = \boldsymbol V_1^2 + \cdots + \boldsymbol V_n^2\sim\chi^2_n. \]

UrmƒÉtorul rezultat, cunoscut sub denumirea de Teorema lui Cochran, asigurƒÉ cƒÉ descompunerea unui vector gaussian √Æn componente independente pe subspa»õii ortogonale ne dƒÉ vectori independen»õi a cƒÉror reparti»õie o putem explicita. AceastƒÉ teoremƒÉ poate fi vƒÉzutƒÉ »ôi ca o generalizare a Teoremei lui Pitagora:

Fie \(\boldsymbol Y \sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\mu, \sigma^2 I_n)\), \(\mathcal{M}\subset\mathbb{R}^n\) un subspa»õiu de dimensiune \(p\), \(P\) matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}\) »ôi \(P_\perp = I_n - P\) matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}^\perp\). Au loc urmƒÉtoarele proprietƒÉ»õi:

  1. \(P\boldsymbol Y\sim\mathcal{N}(P\boldsymbol\mu, \sigma^2 P)\) »ôi \(P_\perp\boldsymbol Y\sim\mathcal{N}(P_\perp\boldsymbol\mu, \sigma^2 P_\perp)\)

  2. vectorii \(P\boldsymbol Y\) »ôi \(P_\perp\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol Y - P\boldsymbol Y\) sunt independen»õi

  3. \(\frac{\lVert P(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)\rVert^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi_p^2\) »ôi \(\frac{\lVert P_\perp(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol\mu)\rVert^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi_{n-p}^2\).

Acum avem instrumentele necesare pentru a deduce reparti»õiile estimatorilor √Æn modelul gaussian de regresie liniarƒÉ.

ConsiderƒÉm modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\), sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2'\). DacƒÉ presupunem cƒÉ varian»õa \(\sigma^2\) este cunoscutƒÉ atunci au loc proprietƒÉ»õile

  1. Vectorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian de medie \(\boldsymbol \beta\) »ôi matrice de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(\sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), i.e.¬†\(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1})\)

  2. \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) »ôi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independen»õi

  3. \([n-(p+1)]\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}\)

  1. Pentru a arƒÉta cƒÉ vectorul \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian vom folosi expresia acestuia ob»õinutƒÉ prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon) = \boldsymbol \beta + (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol \varepsilon. \]

Conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2'\), \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2 I_n)\) este un vector gaussian prin urmare »ôi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol \beta + \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{\boldsymbol A} \boldsymbol \varepsilon\) este tot un vector gaussian repartizat

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = \boldsymbol \beta + \underbrace{(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{\boldsymbol A} \boldsymbol \varepsilon = \boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol A\boldsymbol \varepsilon \sim \mathcal{N}\left(\boldsymbol \beta, \boldsymbol A \sigma^2 I_n\boldsymbol A^\intercal\right) = \mathcal{N}\left(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right) \] deoarece \(\boldsymbol A \sigma^2 I_n\boldsymbol A^\intercal = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal \sigma^2 I_n \boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1} = \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\).

  1. Fie \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) subspa»õiul lui \(\mathbb{R}^n\) generat de coloanele matricei \(\boldsymbol X\) »ôi fie \(P_{X} = \boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\) matricea de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\). Avem

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol Y = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal\left(\underbrace{\boldsymbol X(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal}_{=P_X}\right)\boldsymbol Y = (\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol X^\intercal P_X\boldsymbol Y \]

prin urmare \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector aleator ce depinde de \(P_X\boldsymbol Y\). ObservƒÉm de asemenea cƒÉ din defini»õia lui \(\hat{\sigma}^2\),

\[ \hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} = \frac{\lVert \boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)} \] acesta este o func»õie de \(\boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y\). Aplic√¢nd Teorema lui Cochran (de mai sus) observƒÉm cƒÉ vectorii \(P_X\boldsymbol Y\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y\) sunt independen»õi prin urmare »ôi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) »ôi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independen»õi ca func»õii de vectori independen»õi.

  1. Not√¢nd cu \(P_{X^\perp}\) proiec»õia ortogonalƒÉ pe subspa»õiul ortogonal \(\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\), subspa»õiu de dimensiune \(n-(p+1)\), avem

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol\varepsilon} = \boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y = P_{X^\perp}(\underbrace{\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta}_{\in\mathcal{M}(X)} + \boldsymbol \varepsilon) = P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol \varepsilon, \]

unde \(\boldsymbol \varepsilon\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2 I_n)\).

Din Teorema lui Cochran gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ (n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2} = \frac{\lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol \varepsilon\rVert^2}{\sigma^2} = \frac{\lVert P_{X^\perp}\left(\boldsymbol \varepsilon - \mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol \varepsilon]\right)\rVert^2}{\sigma^2}\sim \chi^2_{n - (p+1)}. \]

ConsiderƒÉm modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ \(\boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon\), sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2'\) »ôi presupunem cƒÉ varian»õa \(\sigma^2\) nu este cunoscutƒÉ. Atunci au loc proprietƒÉ»õile

  1. pentru \(j\in\{0,1,\ldots, p\}\), not√¢nd cu \(\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}\) elementul \(j+1\) de pe diagonala matricei \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), avem

\[ \hat{\beta}_j\sim \mathcal{N}(\beta_j, \sigma^2\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}), \quad T_j = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}} = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j}}\sim t_{n-(p+1)} \]

  1. fie \(R\in\mathcal{M}_{q,p+1}(\mathbb{R})\) o matrice de rang \(q\) (\(q\leq p+1\)) atunci

\[ \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \sim F_{q, n - (p+1)} \]

  1. Din exerci»õiul am vƒÉzut cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\sim\mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1})\) prin urmare

\[ \hat{\beta}_j\sim \mathcal{N}(\beta_j, \sigma^2\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}) \]

ceea ce implicƒÉ \(\frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\sigma\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,1)\).

Scriind

\[ T_j = \frac{\frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\sigma\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}}{\frac{\hat{\sigma}}{\sigma}} = \frac{\frac{\hat{\beta}_j - \beta_j}{\sigma\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}}{\sqrt{\frac{(n - (p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}}{n-(p+1)}}} \]

»ôi »õin√¢nd cont de faptul cƒÉ \((n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}\) iar \(\hat{\beta}_j\) »ôi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independente, deducem cƒÉ \(T_j \sim t_{n-(p+1)}\).

  1. SƒÉ remarcƒÉm cƒÉ matricea \(R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\) pƒÉtraticƒÉ de ordin \(q\) este inversabilƒÉ deoarece matricea \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\) este de rang \(p+1\), \(p+1\geq q\). Cum \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian deducem cƒÉ »ôi \(R\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) este un vector gaussian de medie »ôi matrice de covarian»õƒÉ

\[ R\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\sim\mathcal{N}\left(R\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2 R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1} R^\intercal\right) \]

Astfel (a se vedea rezultatul privind legƒÉtura dintre reparti»õia normalƒÉ »ôi reparti»õia \(\chi^2\) de mai sus)

\[ \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\sim \chi^2_q \]

√én expresia de mai sus, √Ænlocuim pe \(\sigma^2\) cu \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) »ôi »õin√¢nd cont cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) »ôi \(\hat{\sigma}^2\) sunt independente iar \((n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}\sim\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}\) concluzionƒÉm cƒÉ

\[ \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) = \frac{\frac{\frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)}{q}}{\frac{(n-(p+1))\frac{\hat{\sigma}^2}{\sigma^2}}{n-(p+1)}} \sim\frac{\frac{\chi^2_q}{q}}{\frac{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}}{n-(p+1)}} = F_{q, n - (p+1)}. \]

Rezultatele din exerci»õiile anterioare conduc la urmƒÉtoarele intervale (atunci c√¢nd parametrii sunt considera»õi separat) »ôi regiuni de √Æncredere (atunci c√¢nd luƒÉm √Æn calcul mai mul»õi parametrii simultan prin urmare »õinem cont »ôi de dependen»õa dintre ei) pentru parametrii modelului de regresie liniarƒÉ:

  1. Un interval de √Æncredere bilateral de nivel de √Æncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru parametrul \(\beta_j\), \(j\in\{0,1,\ldots,p\}\) este dat de

\[ I_{\beta_j} = \left[\hat{\beta}_j - t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}, \hat{\beta}_j + t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}\right] \] unde \(t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) este cuantila de ordin \(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\) a reparti»õiei Student \(t_{n-(p+1)}\).

  1. Un interval de √Æncredere bilateral de nivel de √Æncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(\sigma^2\) este dat de

\[ I_{\sigma^2} = \left[\frac{[n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2}{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)}, \frac{[n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2}{\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)}\right] \]

unde \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) »ôi \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\left(\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\) sunt cuantilele de ordin \(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\) »ôi respectiv \(\frac{\alpha}{2}\) a reparti»õiei \(\chi^2_{n - (p+1)}\).

  1. O regiune de √Æncredere de nivel de √Æncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(q\) (\(q\leq p+1\)) parametrii \(\beta_j\), nota»õi \((\beta_{j_1},\ldots,\beta_{j_q})\), este datƒÉ de
  • atunci c√¢nd \(\sigma\) este cunoscutƒÉ, de

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(R\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\{R\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^q\,|\, \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \leq \chi^2_q(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

  • atunci c√¢nd \(\sigma\) este necunoscutƒÉ, de

\[ RC^{1-\alpha}(R\boldsymbol \beta) = \left\{R\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^q\,|\, \frac{1}{q\hat{\sigma}^2}\left(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta)\right)^\intercal\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) \leq F_{q, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \]

unde \(R\) este o matrice de dimensiune \(q\times(p+1)\) cu toate elementele nule except√¢nd elementele \(R_{i,j_i}\) care sunt egale cu \(1\).

Ca ilustrare a regiunii de √Æncredere de mai sus, sƒÉ presupunem cƒÉ \(p\geq 2\) »ôi \(q = 2\) iar matricea \(R\) este

\[ R = \begin{pmatrix}1 & 0 & 0 & \cdots & 0\\ 0 & 1 & 0 & \cdots & 0\end{pmatrix} \]

ceea ce conduce la \(R(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta} - \boldsymbol\beta) = \begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix}\). DacƒÉ presupunem cƒÉ \(\sigma^2\) este necunoscut atunci regiunea de √Æncredere pentru \((\beta_0,\beta_1)\) este datƒÉ de

\[ \small RC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_0,\beta_1) = \left\{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}^2\,|\, \frac{1}{2\hat{\sigma}^2}\begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0 & \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix}\left[R(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}R^\intercal\right]^{-1}\begin{pmatrix}\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0\\ \hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1\end{pmatrix} \leq F_{2, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \normalsize \]

»ôi not√¢nd cu \(c_{ij}\) elementul de pe linia \(i\) coloana \(j\) a matricei \((\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\), gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ \scriptsize RC^{1-\alpha}(\beta_0,\beta_1) = \left\{(\beta_0,\beta_1)\in\mathbb{R}^2\,|\,\frac{c_{22}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)^2 - 2c_{12}(\hat{\beta}_0 - \beta_0)(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1) + c_{11}(\hat{\beta}_1 - \beta_1)^2}{2\hat{\sigma}^2(c_{11}c_{22} - c_{12}^2)}\leq F_{2, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\right\} \normalsize \]

ceea ce aratƒÉ cƒÉ regiunea are formƒÉ de elipsƒÉ (vezi (Ornea and Turtoi 2000, Capitolul 2, Sec»õiunea 16)).

Fie \((x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\) o nouƒÉ observa»õie »ôi considerƒÉm \(\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal = (1, x_{n+1,1}, \ldots, x_{n+1,p})\). Ne propunem sƒÉ prezicem valoarea \(y_{n+1}\) conform modelului

\[ y_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\boldsymbol \beta + \varepsilon_{n+1} \]

cu \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma^2)\) independentƒÉ de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\).

ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ un interval de √Æncredere de nivel de √Æncredere \(1-\alpha\) pentru \(y_{n+1}\) este dat de

\[ \scriptsize \left[\boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} - t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}, \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal \hat{\boldsymbol \beta} + t_{n-(p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}\right] \normalsize \]

Plec√¢nd de la un e»ôantion de talie \(n\), \((\boldsymbol x_1, y_1), \ldots, (\boldsymbol x_n, y_n)\), gƒÉsim estimatorul de verosimilitate maximƒÉ (acela»ôi cu cel ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate) \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) a lui \(\boldsymbol\beta\) cu ajutorul cƒÉruia putem prezice valoarea \(\hat{y}_{n+1}\) dupƒÉ rela»õia

\[ \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}. \]

Pentru a cuantifica eroarea de predic»õie \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) folosim urmƒÉtoarea descompunere

\[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}, \]

care este o sumƒÉ de douƒÉ variabile gaussiene independente, \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) »ôi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) care este un vector gaussian care depinde de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\). Prin urmare \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}\) este un vector gaussian »ôi »õin√¢nd cont cƒÉ matricea de varian»õƒÉ-covarian»õƒÉ \(Var(\hat{\varepsilon}_{n+1}) = \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right)\) avem

\[ y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} \sim \mathcal{N}\left(0, \sigma^2\left(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}\right)\right). \] AceastƒÉ rela»õie se rescrie sub forma

\[ \frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\sigma\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}} \sim \mathcal{N}(0, 1) \]

»ôi √Ænlocuind \(\sigma\) cu estimatorul sƒÉu \(\hat{\sigma}\) ob»õinem

\[ \frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}} = \frac{\frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\sigma\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}}}{\frac{\sigma}{\hat{\sigma}}} = \frac{\frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\sigma\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}}}{\sqrt{\frac{\frac{[n - (p+1)]\sigma}{\hat{\sigma}}}{n - (p+1)}}} \sim \frac{\mathcal{N}(0,1)}{\sqrt{\frac{\chi^2_{n-(p+1)}}{n - (p+1)}}}. \]

RemarcƒÉm cƒÉ numƒÉrƒÉtorul »ôi numitorul sunt variabile aleatoare independente deoarece \(y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1} = \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal\left(\boldsymbol \beta - \hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\right) + \varepsilon_{n+1}\) este independentƒÉ de \(\hat{\sigma}\) pentru cƒÉ \(\hat{\sigma}\) este independentƒÉ de \(\hat{\boldsymbol \beta}\) »ôi de \(\varepsilon_{n+1}\) (estimatorul \(\hat{\sigma}\) nu depinde dec√¢t de \(\varepsilon_i\), \(1\leq i\leq n\)). Prin urmare gƒÉsim cƒÉ

\[ \frac{y_{n+1} - \hat{y}_{n+1}}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{(1 + \boldsymbol x_{n+1}^\intercal(\boldsymbol X^\intercal \boldsymbol X)^{-1}\boldsymbol x_{n+1}}} \sim t_{n-(p+1)} \]

de unde rezultƒÉ intervalul de √Æncredere dorit.

2.4.2 Testare de ipoteze statistice

ConsiderƒÉm modelul de regresie liniarƒÉ

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta + \boldsymbol \varepsilon \]

sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2': \, \boldsymbol \varepsilon \sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I_n)\). √én particula, acest model ne spune cƒÉ \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathcal{M}(X)\) unde \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) este subspa»õiul de dimensiune \(p+1\) a lui \(\mathbb{R}^n\) generat de coloanele matricei de design \(\boldsymbol X\).

Pentru √Ænceput, √Æn aceastƒÉ sec»õiune ne propunem sƒÉ testƒÉm dacƒÉ ultimii \(q\) coeficien»õi, \(q = p + 1 - p_0\leq p+1\), sunt nuli, altfel spus vrem sƒÉ testƒÉm ipotezele

\[ H_0:\, \beta_{p_0+1} = \cdots = \beta_p = 0 \quad \text{versus}\quad H_1:\,\exists j\in\{p_0+1,\ldots,p\}\, \beta_j\neq 0 \]

√én termeni de model, ipoteza \(H_0\) ne spune cƒÉ modelul revine la

\[ \boldsymbol Y = \boldsymbol X_0\boldsymbol \beta_0 + \boldsymbol \varepsilon_0 \]

sub ipotezele \(\mathcal{H}_1: \, rang(\boldsymbol X_0) = p_0\) »ôi \(\mathcal{H}_2': \, \boldsymbol \varepsilon_0 \sim\mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I_n)\), unde matricea \(\boldsymbol X_0\in\mathcal{M}_{n,p_0}(\mathbb{R})\) este compusƒÉ din primele \(p_0\) coloane ale lui \(\boldsymbol X\) iar \(\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathcal{M}_{p_0,1}(\mathbb{R})\). Fie \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) subspa»õiul lui \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) de dimensiune \(p_0\) generat de coloanele lui \(\boldsymbol X_0\) (deoarece \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X) = p+1\) deducem cƒÉ \(\mathrm{rang}(\boldsymbol X_0) = p_0\)). Sub ipoteza \(H_0\) avem cƒÉ \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol X_0\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)\).

Sub ipoteza \(H_0\) statistica de test

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{q}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2} = \frac{n - (p+1)}{q}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS} \sim F_{q, n - (p+1)} \]

unde \(F_{q, n - (p+1)}\) este reparti»õia lui Fisher cu \((q, n - (p+1))\) grade de libertate.

  1. Abordarea geometricƒÉ

Vom prezenta mai jos o abordare din punct de vedere geometric a problemei de testare. ConsiderƒÉm spa»õiul \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\subset\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi am vƒÉzut cƒÉ sub ipoteza nulƒÉ avem \(\mathbb{E}[\boldsymbol Y] = \boldsymbol X_0\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)\). √én aceastƒÉ situa»õie, metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate consistƒÉ √Æn proiectarea lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) pentru a ob»õine \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) (vezi figura de mai jos).

Ideea procedurii de testare, »ôi prin urmare a deciziei de a respinge sau nu ipoteza nulƒÉ, este urmƒÉtoarea: dacƒÉ proiec»õia \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) este aproape de proiec»õia \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) a lui \(\boldsymbol Y\) pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) atunci nu respingem ipoteza nulƒÉ, √Æn caz contrar o respingem √Æn favoarea alternativei \(H_1\). De fapt, dacƒÉ informa»õia adusƒÉ de cele douƒÉ modele nu diferƒÉ foarte mult atunci este recomandat sƒÉ pƒÉstrƒÉm modelul mai simplu (principiul parcimoniei).

Pentru a cuantifica apropierea dintre cele douƒÉ proiec»õii putem considera distan»õa euclidianƒÉ \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2\) dintre acestea. AceastƒÉ distan»õƒÉ variazƒÉ √Æn func»õie de datele »ôi de unitƒÉ»õile de mƒÉsurƒÉ a acestora »ôi pentru a evita aceastƒÉ problemƒÉ de scarƒÉ se recomandƒÉ standardizarea acestei distan»õe prin √ÆmpƒÉr»õirea ei la pƒÉtratul normei erorii reziduale \(\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\rVert^2 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = [n - (p+1)]\hat{\sigma}^2\). Cum vectorii aleatori \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) »ôi \(\hat{\boldsymbol \varepsilon}\) nu apar»õin √Æn subspa»õii de aceea»ôi dimensiune trebuie sƒÉ √Æi √ÆmpƒÉr»õim »ôi prin gradele de libertate corespunzƒÉtoare, respectiv \(q = p+1 - p_0\) »ôi \(n - (p+1)\). Ob»õinem astfel statistica de test

\[ F = \frac{\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{p+1-p_0}}{\frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2}{n - (p+1)}} = \frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2}. \]

Pentru a putea utiliza aceastƒÉ statisticƒÉ de test este necesar sƒÉ determinƒÉm reparti»õia sa sub ipoteza nulƒÉ. Not√¢nd cu \(P_X\) »ôi respectiv \(P_{X_0}\) matricele de proiec»õie ortogonalƒÉ pe \(\mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\), »ôtim cƒÉ

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 = P_X\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y \]

»ôi cum \(\mathcal{M}(X_0)\subset \mathcal{M}(X)\), deci \(P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y = P_{X_0}P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\) »ôi

\[ \hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 = P_{X}\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y = (I_n - P_{X_0})P_X\boldsymbol Y = P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}\boldsymbol Y. \]

Astfel am gƒÉsit cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)^\perp\cap \mathcal{M}(X)\) »ôi cum \(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\in\mathcal{M}(X)^\perp\) gƒÉsim cƒÉ \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 \perp \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\). Vectorii \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\) »ôi \(\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\) sunt elemente din spa»õii ortogonale ceea ce implicƒÉ \(Cov(\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0, \boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}) - 0\) »ôi cum sunt »ôi vectori gaussieni (conform ipotezei \(\mathcal{H}_2'\)) deducem cƒÉ sunt »ôi independen»õi ceea ce aratƒÉ cƒÉ numƒÉrƒÉtorul »ôi numitorul lui \(F\) sunt independente.

Conform Teoremei lui Cochran avem pentru numitor

\[ \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X^\perp}(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta + \boldsymbol\varepsilon)\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol\varepsilon\rVert^2\sim\chi^2_{n - (p+1)} \]

iar pentru numƒÉrƒÉtor

\[ \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \frac{1}{\sigma^2}\lVert P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}(\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta)\rVert^2 \sim \chi^2_{q} \]

Sub \(H_0\), parametrul \(\lVert P_{X_0}^\perp P_{X}\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2\) este nul deoarece \(\boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\in\mathcal{M}(X_0)\) ceea ce conduce la

\[ F\overset{H_0}{\sim} F_{q, n - (p+1)}. \]

Putem observa de asemenea cƒÉ aplic√¢nd Teorema lui Pitagora

\[\begin{align*} \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 &= \lVert\boldsymbol Y - P_X\boldsymbol Y + P_X\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert (I_n - P_X)\boldsymbol Y + P_{X_0}P_X\boldsymbol Y - P_{X_0}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 \\ &= \lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y + (I_n - P_{X_0})P_X\boldsymbol Y \rVert^2 = \lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y + P_{{X_0}^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y \rVert^2\\ &= \lVert P_{X^\perp}\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 + \lVert P_{{X_0}^\perp}P_X\boldsymbol Y\rVert^2 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 + \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 \end{align*}\]

altfel spus

\[ \lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2 - \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2 = RSS_0 - RSS. \]

Ne propunem sƒÉ testƒÉm ipoteza nulƒÉ \(H_0:\, \beta_j = 0\) versus ipoteza alternativƒÉ \(H_1:\, \beta_j \neq 0\). Propune»õi o procedurƒÉ de testare pentru cele douƒÉ ipoteze.

AceastƒÉ problemƒÉ este un caz particular al rezultatului ob»õinut anterior pentru \(q = 1\). Avem statistica de test

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{1}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2} = \frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\hat{\sigma}^2} \]

cu ajutorul cƒÉreia putem construi regiunea criticƒÉ

\[ C = \{\omega\,|\,F(\omega)>F_{1, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\}. \]

Acest test este echivalent cu testul bazat pe statistica de test repartizatƒÉ student cu \(n - (p+1)\) grade de libertate (mai exact \(F^2 = T_j\))

\[ T_j = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j}{\hat{\sigma}_{\hat{\beta}_j}} = \frac{\hat{\beta}_j}{\hat{\sigma}\sqrt{\left[(\boldsymbol X^\intercal\boldsymbol X)^{-1}\right]_{j+1,j+1}}}. \]

Regiunea criticƒÉ a testului este

\[ C = \left\{\omega\,|\,T_j(\omega)>t_{n - (p+1)}\left(1-\frac{\alpha}{2}\right)\right\}. \]

Aceasta este forma sub care testul de semnificativitate pentru un coeficient apare √Æn R.

Propune»õi o procedurƒÉ de testare pentru ipotezele

\[ H_0:\, \beta_1 = \ldots = \beta_p = 0 \quad \text{versus}\quad H_1:\,\exists j\in\{1,\ldots,p\}\, \beta_j\neq 0 \]

Vrem sƒÉ testƒÉm dacƒÉ variabilele explicative au sau nu influen»õƒÉ asupra variabilei rƒÉspuns, cu alte cuvinte vrem sƒÉ testƒÉm dacƒÉ to»õi coeficien»õii sunt nuli except√Ænd constanta (\(\beta_0\)) - acesta este testul care apare ca rezultat atunci c√¢nd efectuƒÉm sumarul modelului liniar √Æn R (comanda summary(model)). Suntem √Æn cazul particular √Æn care \(\hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0 = \bar{y}\mathbf{1}\) »ôi ob»õinem statistica de test a lui Fisher (testul global al lui Fisher)

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{p}\frac{\lVert\hat{\boldsymbol Y} - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}_0\rVert^2}{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \hat{\boldsymbol Y}\rVert^2} \sim F_{p, n - (p+1)} \] sau exprimatƒÉ √Æn termeni de coeficient de determinare

\[ F = \frac{n - (p+1)}{p}\frac{R^2}{1 - R^2} \sim F_{p, n - (p+1)}. \]

Vrem sƒÉ testƒÉm ipotezele

\[ H_0:\, \beta_{p_0+1} = \cdots = \beta_p = 0 \quad \text{versus}\quad H_1:\,\exists j\in\{p_0+1,\ldots,p\}\, \beta_j\neq 0 \]

cu ajutorul testului bazat pe raportul de verosimilitƒÉ»õi. ArƒÉta»õi cƒÉ acest test este echivalent cu testul \(F\) al lui Fisher.

Testul bazat pe raportul de verosimilitate este

\[ \Lambda(\mathbf{y})=\frac{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_0}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})}{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})}, \]

unde \(\Theta\) este spa»õiul parametrilor modelului, \(\Theta_0\) este spa»õiul parametrilor corespunzƒÉtor ipotezei nule iar \(L(\theta|\mathbf{x})\) este func»õia de verosimilitate.

ObservƒÉm cƒÉ spa»õiul parametrilor modelului este

\[ \Theta = \left\{(\boldsymbol \beta, \sigma^2)|\,\boldsymbol \beta\in\mathbb{R}^{p+1}, \sigma^2\in (0,\infty)\right\}, \]

cel corespunzƒÉtor ipotezei nule este

\[ \Theta_0 = \left\{(\boldsymbol \beta_0, \sigma^2)|\,\boldsymbol \beta_0\in\mathbb{R}^{p_0}, \sigma^2\in (0,\infty)\right\} \]

iar func»õia de verosimilitate este

\[ L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \prod_{i = 1}^{n}f_{Y}(y_i) = \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\sum_{i = 1}^{n}(y_i - \boldsymbol x_i^\intercal\boldsymbol\beta)^2} = \left(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi\sigma^2}}\right)^n e^{-\frac{1}{2\sigma^2}\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\boldsymbol\beta\rVert^2}. \]

ObservƒÉm cƒÉ

\[ \sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y}) = \sup_{\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2} L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = L(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}, \hat{\sigma}^2_{VM};\boldsymbol Y) \]

unde \(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{VM}=\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\) este estimatorul ob»õinut prin metoda celor mai mici pƒÉtrate iar \(\hat{\sigma}^2_{VM} = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}{n} = \frac{RSS}{n}\). Astfel gƒÉsim

\[ \sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y}) = \sup_{\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2} L(\boldsymbol\beta, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = \left(\frac{n}{2\pi\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}\rVert^2}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}} = \left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}}. \]

Sub \(H_0\) avem

\[ sup_{\theta\in\Theta_0}L(\theta|\mathbf{y}) = \sup_{\boldsymbol\beta_0, \sigma^2\in\Theta_0} L(\boldsymbol\beta_0, \sigma^2;\boldsymbol Y) = L(\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{0}, \hat{\sigma}^2_{0};\boldsymbol Y) = \left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS_{0}}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}} \]

unde \(RSS_0 = \lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X_0\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_0\rVert^2\) iar \(\hat{\sigma}^2_{0} = \frac{\lVert\boldsymbol Y - \boldsymbol X_0\hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_0\rVert^2}{n} = \frac{RSS_0}{n}\).

Prin urmare raportul de verosimilitate devine

\[ \Lambda(\mathbf{y})=\frac{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta_0}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})}{\sup_{\theta\in\Theta}L(\theta|\mathbf{y})} = \frac{\left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS_{0}}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}}}{\left(\frac{n}{2\pi RSS}\right)^{\frac{n}{2}}e^{-\frac{n}{2}}} = \left(\frac{RSS_0}{RSS}\right)^{-\frac{n}{2}} \]

iar regiunea criticƒÉ a testului se scrie (testul respinge ipoteza nulƒÉ atunci c√¢nd statistica \(\Lambda\) este suficient de micƒÉ)

\[ C = \left\{\boldsymbol Y\in\mathbb{R}^n\,|\, \Lambda(\boldsymbol Y)< \lambda_0 \right\}. \] ObservƒÉm cƒÉ pentru \(\lambda>0\), func»õia \(h(\lambda) = \lambda^{-\frac{2}{n}}-1\) este descrescƒÉtoare, adicƒÉ \(\lambda<\lambda_0\) implicƒÉ \(h(\lambda)>h(\lambda_0)\). Avem

\[ h(\lambda)>h(\lambda_0) \iff \frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}>h(\lambda_0) \iff \frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}>f_0 \]

unde \(f_0\) se determinƒÉ din condi»õia

\[ \mathbb{P}_{H_0}\left(\frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}>f_0\right) = \alpha \]

»ôi cum \(\frac{n - (p+1)}{(p+1) - p_0}\frac{RSS_0 - RSS}{RSS}\sim F_{(p+1) - p_0, n - (p+1)}\) conform exerci»õiului deducem cƒÉ \(f_0 = f_{(p+1) - p_0, n - (p+1)}(1-\alpha)\). Am gƒÉsit cƒÉ regiunea criticƒÉ a testului bazat pe raportul de verosimilitate este identicƒÉ cu cea a testului \(F\) a lui Fisher (vezi exerci»õiul ).
